f: BRASS co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the planning and operation of wedding and wedding reception business. The Company mainly operates its business in Tokai region, such as Aichi, Gifu, Mie, Shizuoka. The Company operates wedding segment, which provides full charter type guest house service, and operates one chapel, one party hall, and one kitchen style stores. The Company also provides garden and terrace shows, hall decoration arrangement, as well as complete private space to bride, groom and guests.

NEXTAGE Co., Ltd. is principally engaged in the dealing of used cars. The main businesses of the Company consist of used car store operation, maintenance, insurance agency and automobile dealing, as well as other services, such as used car export and car coating services. The used car store operation business is comprised of domestic general automobiles, light automobiles and imported automobiles. The maintenance business provides vehicle inspection and maintenance services. The insurance agency business offers automobile insurance as an insurance agency. The automobile dealing business mainly purchases vehicles that are no longer needed by its customers. The Company exports used cars mainly to developing countries and emerging countries in east Africa and Oceania. Through its subsidiary, it provides car coating services, which makes car bodies hydrophilic and durable to dirt, acid and ultraviolet degradation. It also involves in new car dealer operation business.

Meito Sangyo Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company principally engaged in the manufacture and sale of food products. The Company operates in three business segments. The Food segment provides chocolates, baumkuchens, powdered beverages, jellies, candies and ice creams. The Chemicals segment provides pharmaceuticals, mixture feed and enzymes, among others. The Real Estate segment is primarily involved in the operation of golf courses and the leasing of real estate properties. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had three subsidiaries and three associated companies.

GOLF DO CO., LTD. is a company mainly engaged in the operation of direct and franchised chain (FC) stores that purchase and sell secondhand golf clubs. The Company gives rights to use its brand name and trade name, sells goods and provides services to franchise members. Its products include new and secondhand golf clubs, golf goods, such as golf- balls, caddy bags, gloves, shoes and apparel, as well as the provision of services, such as grip exchange, shaft exchange, lie angle adjustment and in-store golf lessons, among others. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had two consolidated subsidiaries. On April 2, 2014, the Company established a wholly owned subsidiary engaged in marketing research and support business in Saitama. On May 8, 2014, the Company sold a subsidiary engaged in development and sale of supplement and health food.

TOKEN CORPORATION is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the construction business. The Company is active in business segments. The Construction segment is engaged in the planning, proposal, design and construction of apartments, condominiums for rent, one-year condominiums, senior condominiums and stores, as well as the production, processing and sale of construction materials. This segment is also engaged in the loan business, as well as the provision of life and non-life insurance agency services. The Real Estate Leasing segment is involved in the leasing of real estate, the lease agency of buildings built by the Company and other general residential buildings, as well as the management of leased properties. The Others segment involves in the provision of advertising agency services and travel agency services, as well as the operation of golf courses and country clubs.

BRONCO BILLY Co., LTD. is a Japan-based company engaged in the operation of chain restaurants. The Company principally provides steaks, hamburgers and salad in its restaurants under the name of BRONCO BILLY. The Company is also engaged in the processing of steaks and hamburgers through its food processing factory, as well as the delivery of fresh vegetables. As of December 31, 2012, the Company operated 70 restaurants in Aichi, Gifu, Mie, Shizuoka, Kanagawa and Saitama Prefectures and Tokyo Metropolitan.

CHUOH PACK INDUSTRY CO., LTD. is principally engaged in the manufacture and sale of packing materials and chemical products. The Company is engaged in the manufacture and sale of corrugated boards for electronic products, vehicle components and others. The Company is also engaged in transportation business, waste paper business, as well as storage and cargo handling businesses. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had four subsidiaries and four associated companies.

IMURAYA GROUP CO., LTD. is engaged in the manufacture and sale of foodstuffs. The Company operates in three business segments. The Distribution segment manufactures and sells confectioneries and frozen desserts, as well as operates American style restaurants under the name of Anna Miller's, and stores under the name of JOUVAUD. The Seasoning segment provides various seasonings. The Others segment is involved in the management of real estate properties, the non-life insurance agency business and the leasing agency business, as well as the leasing of real estate, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had nine subsidiaries.

Shin-Etsu Chemical Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in chemical business. The Company operates in six business segments. The Poly Vinyl Chloride and Chemicals segment manufactures and sells vinyl chloride, caustic soda products, chloromethane and methanol. The Silicon segment manufactures and sells silicon products. The Functional Chemicals segment manufactures and sells cellulose derivatives, metal silicon, poval and synthetic sex pheromone. The Semiconductor Silicon segment manufactures and sells semiconductor silicon products. The Electronic and Functional Materials segment manufactures and sells rare earth magnet, packaging materials for Light Emitting Diode (LED), photoresists, mask blanks, synthetic quartz products, liquid fluoroelastomer and pellicle. The Others Related segment provides resin processed products, exports technology and plant and others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 123 subsidiaries and 14 associated companies.

KAGOME CO., LTD. is a manufacturer and trader of foodstuffs. The Domestic segment has seven divisions. The beverage division offers vegetable drinks, fruit drinks, lactic acid bacteria soft drinks. The food division offers seasonings and heat-and-serve meals. The gift division offers gifts for drinks. The fresh vegetable division produces and sells tomatoes. The mail-order division offers drinks and supplies for mail-order only. The business use division offers seasoning, material and beverage. The others division operates the real estate, logistics and raw material sales businesses. The Overseas segment is engaged in the production and sale of seasonings, frozen vegetables, beverages and fresh tomatoes in the United States, Europe, Asia and Australia. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 32 subsidiaries and three associated companies.

Maruhachi Holdings Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in bedding-living products business, as well as real estate leasing business. The Company is a holding company, engages in the management and operation of subsidiaries. The Company operates its business through two segments. Bedding living supply business is engaged in bedding living supplies product planning, raw material procurement, manufacturing, logistics, sales and related services, mainly provides the manufacture and wholesale of feather bedding, wool bedding, fur products (flooring bedding, rugs). Real estate leasing business engages in the rental of facilities such as tenant buildings for company customers.

CHUCO CO., LTD. is mainly engaged in the operation of media business and advertising sales promotion (SP) business. The Company operates in two business segments. The Media segment is engaged in the publication of free living information magazines, the development, sale and operation of living information portal Website, the planning and operation of trainings, lectures, concerts, symposiums and seminars, the operation of various public relations (PR) and Internet shopping businesses. The Advertising SP segment involves in the selection of media, the proposal of advertising designs, and the planning and operation of sales promotion measures to meet the needs of advertisers, the handling media include the Companyâ€™s own media, as well as televisions, radios, newspapers, magazines, Internet advertising and other publications. The Company also involves in the operation of free magazines ('Tonejin' and 'Cookies') related business.

RESORTTRUST, INC. is a Japan-based company mainly involved in the construction and operation of membership hotels, the sale of membership rights, as well as golf and medical businesses. The Company operates in five business segments. The Membership segment is engaged in the development of membership hotels and the sale of hotel membership rights. The Hotel Restaurant segment is mainly involved in the operation of restaurants and resort hotels under the names XIV, BAYCOURT CLUB, SUN MEMBERS and HOTEL TRUSTY. The Golf segment develops and operates golf courses, as well as sells golf membership rights. The Medical segment is engaged in the sale and management of medical membership rights, as well as the provision of medical consulting services. The Others segment is involved in the leasing of real estate properties and the management of villas. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 24 subsidiaries and eight associated companies.

Takeda Pharmaceutical Company Limited is a Japan-based company engaged in the pharmaceutical business. The Ethical Pharmaceutical segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of pharmaceutical products, such as therapeutic substances for diabetes, circulatory drugs, anticancer drugs, drugs for central neurological diseases, digestive system drugs, hormonal agents, osteoporosis drugs, antibiotic agents, allergy medications, vitamin drops and vaccines, among others. The Healthcare segment manufactures and sells general drugs and medicines, as well as quasi drugs. The Others segment is involved in the manufacture and sale of reagents, clinical diagnostics and chemical products. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 146 subsidiaries and 17 associated companies.

HISAMITSU PHARMACEUTICAL CO., INC. is a pharmaceutical company that operates in two business segments. The Medical and Related Product segment, along with its subsidiaries and associated companies, mainly manufactures and sells pharmaceuticals and related products in Japan, as well as the United States, Brazil, Vietnam, China and Indonesia. The Others segment is engaged in the urban cable television broadcasting business and Internet connection service business, the sale and rearing of experimental animals, the sale of experimental equipment and materials, the purchase, manufacture and sale of packing materials, the non-life insurance agency business and advertising agency business, among others.

Daitobo Co., Ltd., formerly Daito Woolen Spinning & Weaving Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company principally engaged in the manufacture and sale of apparel products and fabrics, as well as real estate business. The Fabrics and Apparel segment has four divisions. The apparel division sells clothing. The uniform division sells uniforms. The materials division sells fabric materials. The bedding division sells bedding products. The Real Estate segment is involved in the rental of real estates, as well as the operation and management of commercial facilities, which are operated by subsidiaries.

KANEKA CORPORATION is a Japan-based chemical company engaged in seven business segments. The Chemical segment offers caustic soda, chloride compounds, vinyl chloride resin, vinyl chloride compounds, specialty vinyl chloride resin and others. The Functional Resin segment provides modifiers, modified silicon polymers and methyl methacrylate (MMA) film. The Form Resin segment offers foamed styrene resin, expanded polyolefin by bead method and extrusion foaming styrene boards. The Food segment produces and sells margarine, shortening, bakery yeast and spices. The Life Science segment provides medical products, medical equipment and functional food materials. The Electronics segment manufactures and sells resistance polyimide film, liquid crystal products, composite magnetic materials and photovoltaic cells. The Synthetic Fiber and Others segment offers acrylic fibers and engineering-related services.

Nippon Commercial Development Co., Ltd. is primarily engaged in real estate business. The Real Estate Investment segment sells the real estate investments developed by the Company to funds, investors and others. It acquires lands, leases to tenants, and then sells to companies, individuals, private funds and real estate investment trusts as investment products that can bring stable profits. The Sublease, Lease and Fund Fees segment is engaged in sublease business, which rents lands from owners and then subleases to tenants, lease business, which leases properties owned by the Company to generate stable rental incomes, and fund fees business, which provides real estate management and others. The Planning and Brokerage segment provides consulting and real estate brokerage. As of March 31, the Company had one subsidiary.

Hinokiya Holdings Co., Ltd., is engaged in contract timbered housing construction business. The Contract Housing Construction segment involves in the design, construction, administration and sale of housing with timber frame construction method. The Real Estate segment involves in the design, construction and sale of detached houses, and trading of lands. The Heat Shield Material segment develops, manufactures and sells foaming shield materials and residential energy-saving components. The Real Estate Leasing segment leases real estate. The Others segment involves in design, construction, administration and sale of rented accommodation, the home renovation works, demolish works and exterior works, the housing franchise chain (FC) business, and the provision of management guidance for small builder's offices. On January 31, 2014, the Company increased its interest in Lifesupport co Ltd from 35.1% to 52.6%. On February 28, 2014, it acquired the entire shares in Hokuto House Industry Ltd.

POVAL KOGYO CO.,LTD. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the manufacture and sale of resin processed products. The Company primarily provides belt-related products, including special belts, functional belts and transmission belts; polishing-related products, including parts of cushioning materials used in glass polishing processing, polishing pads for optical components, as well as other products, such as cushioning materials with urethane foam and others.

JB ELEVEN CO., LTD. is a Japan-based holding company engaged in the operation of restaurants. The Company operates in restaurant business through two divisions. The Quick Service division is mainly engaged in the operation of ramen restaurants under the name Ikkokukaido. The Casual Service division is involved in the operation of Chinese restaurants in casual atmosphere, under the names Long-hu dining, which serves Sichuan-style bean curd and Yangzhou fried rice, among others. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had a total of 73 restaurants.

C-CUBE Corporation is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in communication constructions business. The Company operates in two business segments. The Communications Construction segment, along with its subsidiaries and associated company, constructs telecommunications facilities, as well as leases construction vehicles and others. The Information Service segment is engaged in the proposal, building and sale of systems mainly composed by server and computers, communication systems and peripheral equipment, such as Internet protocol private branch eXchange (IP-PBX), Internet protocol (IP) telephones and cellular phones, as well as the development of software. Through its subsidiary, it also provides temporary staffing services and vehicle leasing services.

NICCA CHEMICAL CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of surfactants. The Company operates in three business segments. The Chemicals segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of surfactants for the textile processing, papermaking and metal industries, as well as commercial detergent, among others. The Cosmetics segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of shampoos, conditioner, hair dyes, styling products and perm solutions, among others. The Others segment is engaged in the contracted construction of facility works. The Company is also engaged in the manufacture and sale of petrochemical products such as coolant agents, polishing agents and others, as well as oil waxes. As of December 31, 2014, the Company had 15 subsidiaries and four associated companies.

YUTAKA FOODS CORPORATION is engaged in the manufacture and sale of food products. The Company operates in four business segments. The Liquid Seasoning Product segment produces eel sauce and liquid Soup. The Powder Food Product segment is engaged in the production of soup powders, granule products and functional food, among others. The Chilled Food Product segment produces yakisoba (Japanese-style fried noodles), raw noodles and Japanese udon noodles, among others. The Instant Noodle segment is engaged in the production of instant noodles. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had two subsidiaries and two associated companies.

International Conglomerate of Distribution for Automobile Holdings Co., Ltd. is a pure holding company. The Company, through its subsidiaries, is principally engaged in the dealing of both new cars and used cars, as well as the recycling of automobile. The Company operates its businesses through two segments. Its automobile sales related business segment is comprised of new car division, which sells and repairs new cars and used cars as a regular dealer; used car division, which sells, purchases and repairs used cars; service division, which provides automobile inspection and maintenance services, as well as others division, which includes car rental and sales business. This segment also sells automobile insurances, such as automobile liability insurance and voluntary insurance, as a casualty insurance agency. Its automobile recycling business segment consists of dismantling of end-of-life vehicles, sale of recycled products, and sale of reused parts.
Auto Vehicles, Parts & Service Retailers - NEC

GFOOT CO., LTD. is primarily engaged in the general retail business with a focus on general merchandising store (GMS). The Company is also involved in the specialty store business, developer business and services business. The Company provides men's shoes, ladies' shoes, sports shoes, athletic shoes, children shoes and imported miscellaneous goods, through specialty shops in shopping centers. As of February 28, 2014, the Company had 735 stores located in Hokkaido area, Tohoku area, Kanto area, Chubu area, Kinki area, Chugoku area, Shikoku area and Kyushu area.

Mitsuchi Corporation is a Japan-based company engaged in the manufacture and sale of automobile parts. The Company offers seat parts, including arms, reclining adjuster rods, slide rollers, location pin strikers, handle shafts for lumbers, hinge pins and shoulder pins; window regulator parts, including handle shafts, gear shafts, pins, roller assemblies and tapping screws for resin; various locks, as well as air bag parts. It also offers quick joints. As of June 30, 2012, the Company had six subsidiaries.

MITACHI CO., LTD is a company mainly involved in the sale of semiconductors, liquid crystal products and electronic parts. The Domestic division is engaged in the purchase and sale of semiconductors, including universal integrated circuits (ICs), diodes, transistors, optical semiconductors and system large-scale integration (LSI); liquid crystal products, such as liquid crystal modules; electronic components, including resistors, condensers, switches and electronic printed boards; industrial equipment, such as chip mounters and printers, as well as other components, such as hard discs and electric motors. The Overseas division is engaged in the contracted manufacture and sale of optical semiconductors, electrical devices and electrical components, as well as the purchase and sale of electrical devices and electrical components. In addition, the Company is engaged in the entrusted print processing and the embedded systems.

SANEI ARCHITECTURE PLANNING CO., LTD. is mainly engaged in the real estate business. The Company operates in three business segments. The Real Estate Sales segment is engaged in the development of detached houses, including the collection of land information, the planning of business revenues and layout, the planning and design of buildings, the purchase of land, the application of development business, the supervision of construction works, the sale of houses, as well as the provision of post-sale maintenance services, among others. The Contract Real Estate segment is involved in the entrusted housing business and the entrusted design and construction of detached houses. The Leasing Revenue segment is engaged in the purchase, leasing and management of commercial and residential properties. On October 1, 2012, the Company established a Japan-based wholly owned subsidiary.

PENTA-OCEAN CONSTRUCTION CO., LTD. is mainly engaged in the construction and development business, as well as the sale of construction materials, equipment leasing and shipbuilding businesses. The Company operates in five business segments. The Domestic Civil Engineering segment conducts civil engineering works in the domestic market. The Domestic Construction segment conducts construction works in the domestic market. The Overseas Construction segment involves in the provision of construction works in overseas markets, and the leasing and management of large-scale navigable dredgers. The Domestic Development segment develops, sells and leases real estate, and leases land and buildings. The Others segment is involved in the office equipment leasing business, shipbuilding business and the environment-related consulting business.

MARUJUN CO., LTD. is primarily engaged in manufacturing and selling stampings for automobiles. The Company operates through six reporting segments. The Marujun segment is engaged in manufacturing and selling body stampings and precision stampings for automobiles, stamping molds, welding jigs, inspection jigs and other devices. The Thailand segment and Guangzhou segment are engaged in manufacturing and selling body stampings for automobiles, stamping molds, welding jigs, inspection jigs and others. The Wuhan segment and Indiana segment are engaged in manufacturing and selling body stampings for automobiles and others. The Four-Wheel Sales segment is engaged in selling and providing services for automobiles that use parts made by the Company, through automobile dealers operated by the Companyâ€™s subsidiary. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had five subsidiaries.

GaiaX Co.Ltd. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the development, design and operation of social media. The Company operates in two business segments. The Social Service segment is engaged in the sale of active server pages (ASP) and packages, entrusted development of community Websites, the provision of content and membership services, as well as the development and provision of groupware. The Entrusted Development segment mainly provides services related to Web system, including consulting services, package solutions, system integration, maintenance and operation services, and develops community Websites. In addition, the Company is also involved in the long-distance ridesharing service business through its subsidiary.

Bridgestone Corporation is engaged in developing, manufacturing and marketing tires and diversified products. The Company operates through two segments: Tires and Diversified Products. The Company's Tires segment offers tires for passenger cars, trucks, buses, motorcycles, construction and mining vehicles, aircraft, and motor cycles, as well as tubes, wheels and related accessories. The Tires segment also includes the retreading business, and automotive maintenance services. The Company's Diversified Products segment offers various categories of products, including chemical products, industrial products, automotive components, construction materials, electronic equipment, sporting goods and bicycles. Many of these products are made from rubber or rubber-derived materials. The Company has over 170 manufacturing plants in approximately 30 countries around the world. It sells products in over 150 countries across the world.

KAWASAKI SETSUBI KOGYO CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company principally engaged in the air conditioning, cooling and heating equipment, water supply and drainage facility, as well as electrical construction works. Through its subsidiary, the Company is also involved in the repair, maintenance and checking of air conditioning facilities and water supply and drainage facilities. The Company operates in three segments, including the Tobu, Chubu and Seibu. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had one subsidiary.

ISHIZUKA GLASS CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of glass container-related products, houseware-related products, paper container-related products, plastic containers-related products and others. The Glass Bottles-related segment manufactures and sells glass containers. Houseware-related segment manufactures and sells glass tableware. The Paper Containers-related segment manufactures and sells paper containers and related filling machines. The Plastic Containers-related segment provides plastic containers. The Others segment manufactures and sells ceramics products and metal caps. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 12 subsidiaries and one associated company.

YOMEISHU SEIZO CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company principally engaged in the production and sale of Yomeishu, as well as facility operation business. The Yomeishu-related segment is involved in the provision of Yomeishu, as well as the manufacture and sale of mineral water, nutritious supplement drink products, as well as other derived wine and food products. The Facility Operation segment is involved in the operation of restaurants. The Others segment is involved in the provision of leasing services of buildings and warehouses, as well as the solar power generation business.

CDS Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company engaged in the documentation, engineering and technical system development businesses. The Documentation segment is involved in the manufacture of various documents including technical materials, educational materials, operation manuals, user instructions, parts guide manuals, maintenance manuals and others, and related businesses based on technical information. The Engineering segment offers support services for product and facility designs in the areas of product development and manufacturing technology, using three-dimensional computer-aided design (3D-CAD) technology, as well as provides related services including analysis, data conversion and data management. The Technical System Development segment is engaged in the development, operation and planning of computer systems, as well as the provision of consulting services. On July 15, 2013, it fully acquired METAFORM LANGUES.

Nippon Air Conditioning Services Co., Ltd., formerly Nippon Air conditioning Services Co., Ltd., is engaged in the maintenance and management of building facilities with a focus on air conditioners, as well as the renovation construction works. The Company also engages in investment, management and technology consultant business through its subsidiary.

DAITO TRUST CONSTRUCTION CO., LTD. is mainly engaged in real estate-related business. The Company operates in four business segments. The Construction segment is engaged in the planning, design and construction of contracted works. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the brokerage, management and leasing of real estates, the production and sale of real estate information magazines, the operation of real estate portal Website and the guarantee trust for leasing building residents. The Financial segment is involved in the construction loan business and fire reinsurance business. The Others segment is engaged in the sale of fuel, the operation of day service centers and hotels, the printing and delivery of documents, the investment in hotel companies and the cultivation of mushroom. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 17 consolidated companies.

MEIKO CONSTRUCTION CO., LTD. is a construction company that operates in two business segments. The Construction segment is involved in the total construction business, including the civil engineering and construction activities. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the purchase and sale of land and buildings, as well as the leasing of offices. This segment is also engaged in the research and measurement of land and buildings, the trade and brokerage of real estate properties, and the provision of non-life insurance agency services, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries and 13 associated companies.

NITTO FC CO., LTD. is a company mainly engaged in the fertilizer business. The Company operates in four business segments. The Fertilizer segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of compound fertilizers, blended fertilizers and other fertilizers. The Trading segment is engaged in the import and sale of fertilizer and industrial materials. The Real Estate Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing of offices, garages, general warehouses, office buildings, shopping center stores and parking lots. The Others segment is involved in the operation of business hotels, the transportation of fertilizer raw materials, fertilizer products and general cargoes, as well as the storage and cargo handling businesses. As of September 30, 2014, the Company had 10 subsidiaries and three associated companies.

CHUBUSHIRYO CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the fodder business. The Company operates in three business segments. The Fodder segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of formula feed products. The Consumer and Products segment is involved in the commissioned production, purchase and sale of animal products, as well as the manufacture and sale of pet food. The Others segment is engaged in the leasing of real estate properties of old factory site, the manufacture and sale of organic fertilizers, the processing and sale of animal products, the development, purchase and sale of livestock equipment, as well as non-life insurance agency business and other businesses. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had nine subsidiaries and two associated companies.

Tokai Senko K.K. is mainly engaged in the processing and sale of various textile products. The Company operates in five business segments. The Dyeing Processing segment is engaged in the dyeing processing, as well as the import and export of textile products and machinery. The Sewing Products Sales segment is engaged in the sale of sewing products. The Nursery Service segment is engaged in the provision of nursery care services. The Warehousing segment is engaged in the provision of warehousing services. The Others segment is involved in the sale of machinery, the leasing of real estate, as well as other businesses. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had seven subsidiaries and one associated company.

NDS CO.,LTD. is mainly engaged in communication infrastructure construction. The Multidiscipline Engineering segment is involved in the design, construction and maintenance of communication cable network equipment, mobile network equipment, electrical equipment, intelligent transportation systems (ITSs) equipment and solar power generation equipment. The Information and Communication Technology segment is involved in the development, design, operation and maintenance of information and communication technology (ICT) services, as well as the manufacturing, sale and repair of communication equipment. This segment is also engaged in the lease of machinery, vehicles, tools equipment and fixtures and the installation and maintenance of semiconductor manufacturing equipment. The Housing and Real Estate segment is involved in the sale of condominium buildings and the leasing and brokerage of real estate. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 28 subsidiaries and seven associated companies.

Members Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company principally providing Internet business support. The Company provides research and consulting services including Web maintenance, Internet advertisement agency services, social media marketing and smart phone services, among others. On May 1, 2014, the Company established a wholly owned subsidiary in Tokyo.

EDION Corporation is a Japan-based company engaged in the sale of consumer electronic products and information communications equipment. The Company operates in two business segments. The Consumer Electronic Product Sales segment is engaged in the sale of consumer electronics through the operation of direct stores, cellular phone specialty stores and franchise stores, as well as mail order sales. The Others segment is engaged in the operation of software specialty stores, toy specialty stores and consumer electronics repair shops, the development and operation of systems, the plan and development of housing accommodation products, the Internet service provider (ISP) business, the cable television (CATV) broadcasting and CATV Internet business, the operation of professional football teams, the main sponsor business, as well as the manufacture and sale of furniture.

The Yokohama Rubber Company, Limited operates in two business segments. The Tire segment mainly manufactures and sells tire tubes, aluminum wheels and automobile products for cars, trucks, buses, construction vehicles and industrial vehicles. The Industrial Goods segment manufactures and sells conveyor belts, rubber plates, hoses, fenders, oil spill booms, marine hoses, moldings, air springs, highway joints, bridge rubber bearings, building seismic isolation laminated rubber, waterproof materials, water stop materials, insulation and vibration control products, adhesives, sealing materials and others. In addition, the Company is also manufactures and sells aviation parts and sports goods, provides information processing services and conducts real estate leasing business. As of December 31, 2014, the Company had 145 subsidiaries and 44 associated companies.

Sumitomo Riko Company Limited, formerly Tokai Rubber Industries, Ltd., is a manufacturer of rubber and resin products for automobile use. The Automobile Supplies segment manufactures anti-vibration rubbers, hoses and interior parts for automotive use. The General Industrial Supplies segment produces precision resin blade roll, high-pressure hoses, rubber seals, anti-vibration rubber and transport hoses, among others. As of March 31, 2014, it had 80 subsidiaries and nine associated companies.

SALA CORPORATION is a company mainly engaged in the energy and engineering businesses. The Company has five business segments. The Energy Supply and Solution segment sells liquefied petroleum (LP), petrochemical products, high-pressure gas and related equipment, and operates petrochemical product transportation, general cargo transportation and property leasing businesses. The Engineering and Maintenance segment is engaged in civil engineering and construction works, the manufacture and sale of construction materials, the maintenance of facilities, and the telecommunication-related equipment works. The Car Life Support segment sells and maintains domestic and imported cars. The Animal Healthcare segment sells equipment for stockbreeding and medical products for animals, and manufactures and sells additives for animal feed. The Hospitality segment operates hotel and beverage businesses. On April 30, 2014, the Company established a 60%-owned subsidiary in Aichi, Japan.
Oil & Gas Refining and Marketing - NEC

YAHAGI CONSTRUCTION CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the construction businesses. The Company operates in three business segments. The Construction segment is engaged in the contract construction, building renovation, construction machinery leasing and sales, seismic capacity evaluation and consulting, and other seismic strengthening services offering. The Civil Engineering segment is engaged in civil engineering and railway construction, landscaping, golf course maintenance and management, as well as road pavement. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the development, sale and leasing of real estates, the subdivision of condominiums, and the management of buildings and condominiums. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had eight subsidiaries.

ESPOIR Co., Ltd., formerly GEO ESTATE Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company engaged in the planning, development and sale of real estate. The Company mainly operates in two business segments. The Development and Sale segment is involved in the development of condominiums, building land and commercial facilities, as well as the purchase and resale of real estate properties developed by others. The Leasing and Management segment is engaged in the leasing of land and buildings, as well as the leasing and management of commercial facilities. On January 30, 2014, the Company sold a property located in Akita, Japan.

Taisei Corporation is engaged in civil engineering, building construction and real estate development business. The Company's segments include Civil engineering, Construction contracts, Real estate development and Others. The Civil engineering segment is engaged in delivering construction of civil engineering. The Construction contracts segment is engaged in delivering construction of building and housing. The Real estate development segment is engaged in delivering purchase, sale and rental of land and buildings. The Company has branches in Tokyo, Osaka, Nagoya, Fukuoka, Sapporo, Sendai, Hiroshima, Yokohama, Niigata, Takamatsu, Chiba, Saitama, Kobe and Kyoto. The Company offers a range of solutions, including T-iROBO Roller & Breaker, T-SPD, T-WELL_PLANNER, T-Clean Air Wall, T-Mark. Navi, and CF Panel Work Method. It also provides Urban-style Small Displacement Seismic Isolation System, T-Silent Series, Post-Head-Anchor work method and Residual Deformation Technology.

MIE CORPORATION CO., LTD is a Japan-based holding company primarily engaged in the business strategy and management of its subsidiaries and related business. Through its subsidiaries, the Company is engaged in the manufacture and sale of processed metal products, including stainless-steel pipe joints, industrial joints, architectural joints, flanges and screwed welded joints, as well as prefabricated processed products. In addition, the Company is also engaged in the package, storage and shipping of welded joints and flanges, through one of its subsidiaries.

NORITAKE CO., LIMITED is a company mainly engaged in the industrial equipment, tableware, ceramics materials and engineering businesses. The Company has four business segments. The Industrial Equipment segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of abrasive wheels, diamond tools and abrasive cloth/paper. The Ceramic Materials segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of electronic paste, ceramic materials and parts, fluorescent display tubes, as well as dental-related products. The Engineering segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of various industrial furnaces. The Tableware segment is mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of china tableware. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 23 subsidiaries and nine associated companies.

NITTO SEIMO CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the manufacture and sale of fishing nets. The Company operates in three business segments. The Fishing Industry-related segment manufactures and sells various types of fishing nets. This segment also purchases and sells fishing-related labor-saving equipment, fishing boats, ropes, floats and antifoulants. The Land-related segment is involved in the purchase and sale of ropes, and nets for protection from animals and insects, as well as the provision of knotless nets to golf driving ranges and the designing, construction, processing and sale of various sports nets. Additionally, this segment purchases and sells agricultural materials, such as potting compost. The Others segment is engaged in the manufacture and repair of machinery, such as netting machines, as well as transportation equipment. As of April 30, 2014, the Company had nine subsidiaries and two associated companies.

CommSeed Corporation is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the provision of contents and the delivery of information. The Mobile segment is engaged in the operation of Websites for mobile phones, the development and sale of applications for smart phones, the operation and provision of social game applications for social networking service (SNS), as well as the operation of supporting portal Website under the name P-DEPOT through its agents.

TAISEI CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the building maintenance business. The Company operates in five business segments. The Clean segment is engaged in the cleaning management for office buildings, hotels and other buildings. The Facility Management segment is involved in the operational management and maintenance of facilities, including electrical equipment, air conditioning equipment, water supply and drainage, as well as lifting equipment. The Security segment provides safety and security services. The Renewal segment is engaged in the repair work, as well as diagnosis, investigation, planning, design and construction work. The Real Estate Solution segment is engaged in the property management, designated manager and private finance initiative (PFI) businesses.

Gifu landscape architect Co.,Ltd. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in design, construction and maintenance of green landscaping. The Company's businesses are divided into garden exterior business and landscape business by properties. Landscape is a public space that an unspecified number of people visit. The business contains public works, private construction works, as well as maintenance of green space after construction and installation. Garden exterior is a combination of garden/yard and the exterior/outer structure. The business contains co-design and construction of a new large-scale subdivision by the housing manufacturers, as well as the showroom expansion business under the name of Pines to general customers.

Aica Kogyo Company, Limited is a manufacturing company. The Company operates in four business segments. The Chemical Product segment offers interior and exterior finishing materials, flooring materials, adhesives and organic solids. The Construction Material segment offers melamine facing plates and coated plywood boards. The Housing Construction Material and Equipment segment offers doors, interior materials, counters and nonflammable dressed lumbers. The Electronics segment offers electronic materials. The Company also engages in extruded cement board business, calcium silicate board business, multi-functional building materials business.

YAMAURA CORPORATION is a construction company. The Company operates in three business segments. The Construction segment is involved in the newly building, extension and reconstruction of private offices, factories and shops, the construction of housing and condominiums, and the public building construction works. The segment is also engaged in the general civil engineering works, bridge works, snow shelter works, as well as pavement, landscaping and water supply works. The Engineering segment designs, manufactures, installs and maintains automatic controlling equipment, information and communications equipment, water management equipment, industrial machinery, bridge superstructures and high-speed dryers. The Development and Others segment is engaged in the sale and leasing of real estate, the development of building lands, as well as the condominium business, among others. As of September 30, 2014, the Company had one consolidated subsidiary and one affiliated company.

MARUSAN-AI CO., LTD. is a food processing company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of soybean paste, soybean milk and other beverages. The Company operates in three business segments. The Soybean Paste segment is engaged in the development, manufacture and sale of soybean paste, including fresh soybean paste, prepared soybean paste and instant soybean paste, as well as other related products. The Soybean Milk and Beverage segment is engaged in the development, manufacture and sale of soybean milk and beverages, as well as original equipment manufacturing (OEM) business. The Others segment is engaged in the development, manufacture and sale of other food products. As of September 20, 2012, the Company had three consolidated subsidiaries and one associated company.

OKWave is a company mainly engaged in the operation of online community Website http://okwave.jp, which provides information through questions and answers (Q&A) contents. The Company has two business segments. The Portal segment operates social media, and provides social media, social customer relationship management and social commerce services, including OKWave, ARIGATO, OKMusic, OKBiz and OKCorporation, among others. The Solution segment is mainly engaged in the provision of systems and consulting services. In November 2011, the Company acquired a Tokyo-based company.

ArkCore, Inc. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the purchase and sale of used motorcycles. The Company operates through two business segments. The Used Motorcycle segment provides online assessment services and related contents through its Website bike-kaitori.com and offline stores. This segment sells motorcycles purchased from customers to auction companies and consumers. The GEO Shop segment is engaged in the rental, recycle and sale of digital versatile discs (DVDs), compact discs (CDs), game software and game consoles through franchised stores under the name GEO. On March 10, 2014, the Company transferred all shares in an Osaka-based real estate subsidiary, to an individual. On September 20, 2014, it fully acquired FUKUDA MOTORS CORPORATION.

zetton inc. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the operation of restaurants. The Company operates in three business segments. The Public Facility Development segment is engaged in the operation of restaurants in public facilities, including museums, art galleries, airports and train stations, among others. The Commercial Store Development segment is engaged in the operation of restaurants in commercial stores.

Kirin Holdings Company, Limited is a holding company. The Company is engaged in alcohol beverages, non-alcohol beverages, and pharmaceuticals and bio-chemicals businesses. The Company's segments include Integrated Beverages, Pharmaceuticals and Bio-chemicals, and Others. Its Others segment includes food business, such as dairy products, and others. Its businesses comprise Japan Integrated Beverages, Overseas Integrated Beverages, and Pharmaceuticals and Bio-chemicals. The Japan Integrated Beverages business conducts manufacturing and sales of alcoholic beverages and non-alcoholic beverages in Japan. The Overseas Integrated Beverages business includes Lion Nathan Limited (Lion), Schincariol Participacoes e Representacoes S.A. (Brasil Kirin) and Myanmar Brewery Limited. The Pharmaceuticals and Bio-chemicals business includes Kyowa Hakko Kirin Co., Ltd., ProStrakan Group plc and Kyowa Hakko Bio Co., Ltd.

TISC CO., LTD. is mainly engaged in the development of software, the sale of computer equipment, the operational support of software and the maintenance of computer equipment. The Company has two business segments. The System Development segment is involved in the development and sale of packaged software, and the provision of application service provider (ASP) service, as well as the provision of operational support services. The Commodity segment is engaged in the sale of computer equipment and supplies, the provision of housing and hosting services, as well as the provision of maintenance services for computer equipment.

Densan System Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company engaged in the provision of information services and payment-collection agent services. The Company operates in two business segments. The Information Service segment is engaged in the provision of information processing services utilizing the know-how of operation and management in a variety of platforms; the contracted development of software and dispatching of technicians; the sale of software products and the provision of system integration services, and the sale of system equipment, office automation equipment and other supplies, among others. The Payment-Collection Agent segment is mainly engaged in the provision of payment-collection agent services, domestic and overseas remittance services, paperless settlement services, as well as other services.

ARTGREEN CO.,LTD. is principally engaged in wholesale of fresh flowers focused on phalaenopsis. The Company operates through Wholesale of Fresh Flowers segment. It mainly operates through three divisions: flower business support services, nursery support business and funeral business. Flower business support services division is engaged in fresh flowers order business. Nursery support business division mainly sells seedlings of phalaenopsis to phalaenopsis farmers. Funeral business division mainly sells cut flowers such as chrysanthemums.

TOTO LTD. is engaged in the manufacture and sale of restroom fixtures, bathroom fixtures, kitchen fixtures and others. The Company operates in four business segments. The Domestic Housing Facility segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of rest room products, such as sanitary chinaware, warm wash toilets, and plastic and rubber formed parts; bath, kitchen and wash products, such as plastic bathtubs, unit bath rooms, water faucet hardware and parts, among others. The Oversea Housing Facility segment offers products for restroom, bath and basin use. The New Field segment provides tiles and ceramic products, as well as manufactures and sells tile construction materials and coating materials. The Others segment is engaged in the real estate leasing business. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 53 subsidiaries and five associated companies.

Dynapac Co., Ltd. is mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of packaging materials and its related business. The Packaging Material-related segment manufactures and sells corrugated fiberboard sheets and cases, printed paper products, decorated corrugated fiberboard, paper trays, micro flute corrugated board, offset printings, gravure printings, plastic films, corrugated fiberboard cushions and chemical products, among others. The Real Estate segment is engaged in the leasing of real estate properties. As of December 31, 2012, the Company had 11 subsidiaries and one associated company. In June, 2014, the Company set up a wholly owned subsidiary Dynapac (Philippines) Inc.

AMIYAKI TEI CO., LTD. is engaged in the operation of restaurant chains. The Company has three business segments. The Yakiniku segment operates restaurants under the names Amiyaki Tei and Suehirokan in the central Japan and Kanto areas. The Yakitori segment operates restaurants under the name of Ganso Yakitoriya Minoji in the central Japan. The Others segment operates restaurants under the name of Suehirokan, as well as izakaya (Japanese style bars) under the name of Rakuichi in the Kanto areas. On January 31, 2014, the Company acquired 100% stake of ACT GROUP.

Nisshinbo Holdings Inc. is a holding company with seven segments. The Textile segment manufactures and sells textile products. The Break Products segment provides beak assemblies and friction materials for automobile breaks. The Paper segment offers household paper products, such as tissue paper, kitchen towel, fine paper and artificial paper. The Precision Machine segment involves in the manufacture and sale of mechatronic products, precision parts processing, plastic molding. The Chemical segment offers rigid urethane foam, carbon products, high-performance chemicals. The Electronics segment offers wireless communication equipment, electronic components and others. The Real Estate segment leases buildings and shopping centers, as well as sells residential land. In addition, the Company is also engaged in the wholesale of food, industrial materials and clothing fibers, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 91 subsidiaries and 112 associated companies.

Daiseki Eco. Solution Co., Ltd. is mainly engaged in the recycle business and environmental analysis business. The Company operates in six business divisions. The Soil Pollution Research and Treatment division is engaged in the consulting for contaminated soil research plan, the field investigation, the analysis of sampled soil and the treatment of polluted soil. The Waste Gypsum Board Recycling division manufactures and sells gypsum powder made from waste gypsum board. The Recycle division is engaged in the collection, transportation and fracture treatment of waste fluorescent lamps, as well as the collection and transportation of waste dry cells and waste batteries. The Environment Analysis division is engaged in the analysis of industrial wastes and soil. The BDF division produces bio-diesel fuel from waste edible oil. The Others division is engaged in the operation of leasing condominiums and the sale of products.

Sekisui House, Ltd. is engaged in the home building. The Company is engaged in the business of construction, sale, purchase and administration of residential properties; the design, execution, contracting and super-vision of construction projects, and real estate brokerage and landscaping. Its segments include Custom detached houses, which is engaged in the design, construction and contracting of built-to-order detached houses; Rental housing, which is engaged in the design, construction and contracting of built-to-order properties; Real estate management fees, which is engaged in the sub-lease, management, operation and brokerage of real estate; Houses for sale, which is engaged in the sale of houses and lands; Condominiums, which is engaged in the sale of condominiums; Urban redevelopment, which is engaged in the development of office buildings and commercial facilities, and Overseas businesses, which is engaged in contracting of built-to-order detached houses in overseas market.

NGK SPARK PLUG CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of automobile-related products, as well as semiconductor-related and ceramic-related products. The Company operates in two business segments. The Automobile-related segment manufactures and sells automobile parts including spark plugs, glow plugs, various automobile sensors and ceramic engine parts, among others. The Technical Ceramics-related segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of integrated circuit (IC) packages and semiconductor components. This segment also manufactures and sells cutting instrument for machinery tools, and semiconductor manufacturing equipment parts. In addition, the Company is also engaged in the sale of jigs and tools, the transportation business and the provision of social welfare services. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 36 subsidiaries and seven associated companies.

NGK INSULATORS, LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the provision of ceramic products. The Company operates in three segments. The Electric Power-related segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of electrical insulators and machines, as well as sodium-sulfur (NAS) batteries. The Ceramics segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of automotive ceramics products, as well as general industrial ceramics products and machinery including corrosion-resistant machinery for chemical industry, membrane separation devices for liquid and gas, combustion equipment and refractory materials, among others. The Electronics segment manufactures and sells beryllium rolled copper products, ceramic products for electronics industry and semiconductor manufacturing, and molds. The Company is also engaged in the operation of golf courses. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 65 subsidiaries and four associated companies.

SHIMIZU CORPORATION is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the construction business. The Company operates in two business segments. The Construction segment involves in contracting for building. The Development segment involves in the leasing of land and buildings, as well as the orders for construction work. In addition, the Company is also involved in the sale of construction materials, maintenance and operation of public facilities, as well as the operation of care facility for elderly. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 56 subsidiaries and 10 associated companies.

TOENEC CORPORATION is a company engaged in the equipment work business. The Company operates in two business segments. The Equipment Work segment is involved in the provision of construction work for electricity distribution lines, power-related construction works and general construction works, as well as the construction of air conditioning, sanitary, electrical, communications and firefighting facilities, among others, in China, Philippines and Thailand, through its subsidiaries. The Others segment is involved in the sale of products, the leasing of land and office equipment, the provision of non-life insurance agency services and functional filter cleaning services, the maintenance, management and operation of funeral halls, as well as the construction, inspection and maintenance works of thermal and nuclear power plants. As of March 31, 2014, it had five consolidated subsidiaries and two associated companies.

LECIP HOLDINGS CORPORATION is a Japan-based holding company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of transportation machines. The Company has four business segments. The Transportation Machine segment offers integrated circuit card system equipment for bus uses, as well as in-vehicle lightening equipment. The Sign & Display (S&D) segment offers neon transformers, neon cold cathode lamps (CCLs), light-emitting diode (LED) power supplies and electronic ballasts for outdoor neon signs. The Industrial Machine segment provides barcode reading terminals, uninterruptible power supply (UPS) systems and chargers for battery forklifts, as well as electronics manufacturing services (EMSs). The Others segment is engaged in the leasing of land and buildings. On August 22, 2013, it fully acquired Arcontia International AB from Aveqo Venture AB.

AISIN SEIKI CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company engaged in the manufacture and sale of automobile parts and housing-related equipment. The Company has three business segments. The Automobile Parts segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of engine parts, including water pumps, pistons, intake manifolds and others; drive-train components, including automatic transmissions (ATs), manual transmissions (MTs) and others; brake and chassis parts, such as brake master cylinders, disk brakes and antilock brake systems (ABSs); body parts, such as door locks and power backdoor systems, as well as information parts, including car navigation systems, parking support systems and intelligent parking support systems, among others. The Housing-related Equipment segment is engaged in the provision of shower toilets, beds and gas heater pump air-conditionings (GHPs), among others. The Others segment is engaged in the civil construction business and petroleum sales business.

Toyota Motor Corporation (Toyota) conducts business in the automotive industry. The Company also conducts business in finance and other industries. The Company's segments include Automotive, Financial Services and All Other. Toyota sells its vehicles in approximately 190 countries and regions. Toyota's markets for its automobiles are Japan, North America, Europe and Asia. The Company's Automotive segment includes the design, manufacture, assembly and sale of passenger vehicles, minivans and commercial vehicles, such as trucks and related parts and accessories. The Company's Financial Services segment consists of providing financing to dealers and their customers for the purchase or lease of Toyota vehicles. The All Other segment includes the design, manufacturing and sale of housing, telecommunications and other businesses. Its information technology related businesses include a Web portal for automobile information called GAZOO.com.

Toshiba Corporation is a diversified electric/electronic manufacturer. The Company's segments include Energy & Infrastructure, which includes nuclear power generation systems, thermal power generation systems, fuel cells, power generation, and instrumentation and control systems; Community Solutions, which includes broadcasting system, road equipment systems, water supply and sewerage systems, environmental system, elevators and light emitting diode lights; Healthcare Systems & Services, which includes diagnostic x-ray systems and computerized tomography systems; Electronic Devices & Components, which includes small-signal devices, power devices, optoelectronic devices, storage devices and semiconductor manufacturing equipment; Lifestyle Products & Services, which includes personal computers, televisions, refrigerators, washing machines and home appliance repair services, and Others, including information technology solutions, human resource and payroll systems, and logistics service.

Mitsubishi Heavy Industries, Ltd. is a diversified manufacturer. The Energy and Environment segment offers boilers, turbines, gas turbines, diesel engines, water wheels, windmills, nuclear power equipments, nuclear power peripheral devices, among others. The Traffic and Transportation segment offers various ships, including cruise ships, liquefied natural gas (LNG) ships, liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) ships, car ferry, special purpose vessels, automobile carriers, oil tankers, container ships and others, as well as marine structures, among others. The Defense and Space segment offers ships, fighters, helicopters, aircraft fuselage parts, defense aircraft engines, induction flying objects, torpedoes, among others. The Machinery and Equipment systems segment offers waste treatment and exhaust gas treatment equipments, transportation equipments, steel machinery, compressors, bridges, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 290 subsidiaries and 39 associated companies.

KANEFUSA CORPORATION is a Japan-based company engaged in the manufacture and sale of industrial cutting tools and related products. The Company offers flat-blade knives, cutters, circular saw blades and other products. The flat-blade knives include plywood knives, finishing planes, substitute edge-style planes, electrical planes, veneer lathes, slicer knives, chippers and cutting blades, and other cutting knives and machine parts. The cutter products include chamfer cutters, substitute edge-style cutters, router bits, as well as diamond products, among others. The circular saw blades include chip saws and metal cutting circular saws. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had five consolidated subsidiaries and three non-consolidated subsidiaries. It had operations in Japan, Indonesia, the United States, the Europe, China and others.

CHUO SPRING CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company principally involved in the manufacture and sale of springs, control cables and automobile supplies. The Company and its subsidiaries provide chassis springs, precise springs, cables, gold-plating processing and automobile supplies, as well as design and development services for automobile supplies and reels. The Company is also involved in the transportation of its products. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had 22 subsidiaries and one associated company. In October, 2013, the Company established a China-based wholly owned subsidiary Xiaogan Zhongxing Automotive Components Co., Ltd. On July 20, 2014, the Company increased stake in a China-based joint venture from 46.00% to 61.55%.

MARUWA CO., LTD. is a company mainly engaged in manufacture and sale of ceramic products and lighting equipment. The Ceramic Parts segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of ceramic parts including alumina substrates, aluminum nitride substrates, alumina zirconia substrates, silicon nitride substrates, quartz glass products, automotive magnet products, medical ceramic products, faucet ceramic products, antenna module substrates, microwave components, chip varistors, sintered magnetic substrates and power inductors, among others. The Lighting equipment segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of light-emitting diode (LED) lighting equipment for roads, tunnels, streets and squares, among others. As of March 31, 2014, it had 19 subsidiaries and one affiliated company.

Daido Metal Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company engaged in the manufacture and sale of bearings. The Company operates primarily in three business segments. The Automobile Engine Bearing segment and Automobile Bearing (Except Engine) segment are involved in the manufacture and sale of bearings for automobile engines, as well as pump bushes for power steering and bearings for turbo chargers. The Non-Automobile Bearing segment offers bearings for ship engines, power generators, high-speed vehicles, railways, office equipment and dome arenas. This segment also offers rotary pumps and lubricating equipment. The Company also provides storage, delivery and real estate leasing services. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had 24 subsidiaries and one associated company. On January 6, 2014, the Company established a Mexico-based wholly owned subsidiary, Daido Metal Mexico Sales, S.A. de C.V.

Fujitsu Limited is engaged in the business of development, manufacture, sales and maintenance of a range of products and electronic devices. The Company is engaged in providing solutions in the field of information and communication technology. The Company's segments are Technology Solutions, Ubiquitous Solutions, Device Solutions and Others. The Company offers business services, application services, managed infrastructure services and product support services. It also offers solutions, including infrastructure solutions, which consist of various information technology (IT) components; industry solutions, which include automotive, financial services, manufacturing, retail, telecommunications, life science solutions and healthcare, and business and technology solutions, which include smart mobility, technical computing, high performance computing (HPC) and security solutions. Its Others segment includes operations, such as next-generation supercomputer project and facility services.

FUJIMI INCORPORATED is a Japan-based company engaged in the manufacture and sale of abrasive materials. The Company offers products involved in the ingot slice of single crystal silicon, lapping and polishing process, abrasives such as CMP slurry (polishing) which involves in the manufacture of semiconductor devices, abrasive involved in the magnetic disk of hard disk drives, various materials that are used in electronic components, and thermal spray material corresponding to the engine, among others. The Company operates in four geographical regions, including Japan, North America, Asia, and Europe. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had five subsidiaries.

TSUNODA CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the real estate leasing business and bicycle business. The Company is involved in the leasing of land, stores, condominiums, parking lots and others, as well as the planning, development and sale of bicycles. The Company principally sells city bicycles, kids bicycles, mini bicycles, sporting bicycles, special bicycles and bicycle components, among others. The Company also has an affiliated company, which is engaged in the management of real estate properties. As of June 30, 2014, the Company had one affiliated company.

GENERAL PACKER CO., LTD. is a company engaged in the manufacture, sale and repair of automatic packing machinery and peripheral equipment for foods, chemicals and medical products, among others. The Company principally offers custom-made machines to food, chemical and pharmaceutical manufacturing companies. The machinery includes pouch dispensing automatic packaging machines, which are used for products in powder and solid forms; packing machines with bag-making devices, which are used for sack packing and high-speed pouch packing; packing-related equipment, such as filling machines, weighing machines, printing machines and inspection machines, as well as can packing systems and box packing systems, among others. In addition, the Company provides post-sale maintenance and repair services, and sells replacement parts.

THE JAPAN STEEL WORKS, LTD. is mainly engaged in industrial machinery business. It has three business segments. The Forging and Energy segment manufactures and sells iron and steel products, chemical machinery, nuclear power-related machinery, metallic mold, petroleum refinery, petrochemistry, general chemical products, pressure containers, clad plates, various steel pipes and wind generated power machinery. The Industry Machinery segment manufactures and sells plastic injection machines, resin manufacturing and processing machinery, hollow molding machines, fluid machines, hydraulic equipment, electronic equipment and display manufacturing equipment, magnesium alloy injection machines and various other machinery. The Real Estate and Others segment is engaged in the real estate leasing and development businesses, as well as the provision of other operation supports, among others.

Howa Machinery, Ltd. is a manufacturer of machine tools, firearms, construction equipment and materials. The Machine Tool-related segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of machine tools. The Firearm segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of firearms. The Construction Equipment segment provides construction equipment. The Construction Material segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of construction materials. The Real Estate Rental segment is engaged in the rental of lands and buildings. The Domestic Sales Subsidiaries segment is engaged in the sale of steel through domestic subsidiaries. The Others segment is engaged in the solar power generation business and others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries and one associated company.

Mie Kotsu Group Holdings, Inc. is a Japan-based holding company. The Transportation segment is involved in bus, taxi and railway transportation businesses, as well as automobile maintenance business. The Real Estate segment is involved in the trading and leasing of real estates. The Petroleum Product Distribution segment is involved in the sale of petroleum products. The Commodity Distribution segment is engaged in the sale of commodities. The Leisure and Service segment is involved in travel, roadside restaurant, hotel and sightseeing highline businesses, as well as operation of golf courses and driving schools. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had 22 subsidiaries and three associated companies.

J. FRONT RETAILING Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based holding company. The Company operates in five business segments. The Department Store segment is engaged in the sale of clothing products, housewares, food products, miscellaneous goods and others, as well as the operation of dining halls, cafes and tea shops, among others. The Parco segment is engaged in the development, operation, management of shopping centers. The Wholesale segment provides chemical products and materials, food, electrical appliances and electronics. The Credit segment is engaged in the issuance and operation of credit cards. The Others segment is engaged in mail-order business, the leasing of real estate and parking lots, the contract construction works, the manufacture and sale of furniture, among others.

IBIDEN CO., LTD. is primarily engaged in the manufacture of electronic products. It operates in five business segments. The Electronics segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of printed circuit boards (PCBs) and package substrates, as well as the design of PCB patterns. The Ceramics segment offers environment related ceramic products, special carbon products, fine ceramic products and ceramic fibers. The Construction Material segment provides housing equipment, melamine facing plates and decorative laminated sheets processing materials. The Construction Material segment is engaged in the design and construction of slopes, garden landscape and various facilities. The Others segment is involved in other business activities, including synthetic plastic processing, agricultural seafood processing, information service business, automobile transportation, oil marketing, investment, and financing.

OSG CORPORATION is primarily engaged in manufacturing and selling precision machine tools. The Companyâ€™s products include cutting tools, rolling tools, measuring tools, machine parts and others. The Company operates in four segments, including Japan, Americas, Europe and Asia. Each segment is primarily engaged in manufacturing and selling precision machine tools. As of November 30, 2013, the Company had 60 subsidiaries and three associated companies.

NITTOH CORPORATION is a construction company that has three business segments. The Construction Work segment is engaged in utilities construction including gas-related housing facilities, photovoltaic generation systems, air-conditionings, water supply and sewerages; various reform work including construction, design, construction management of detached housing, the sale, mediation, renovation of real estate, care and earthquake resistant reform work. This segment is also engaged in the water proofing construction, such as fiber-reinforced plastic (FRP) and sheet water proofing, revamping water proofing, and others. The Housing Service segment offers services such as the prevention, eradication and re-prevention of termites, the prevention of moisture, the control of pests, as well as the cleaning of housing, offices and stores. The Building Maintenance segment provides cleaning services for building windows and outer walls, as well as condominiums and public facilities.

USS Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company principally engaged in the automobile auction business. The Company operates in three business segments. The Automobile Auction segment is engaged in the provision of three ways to take part in its automobile auctions, including on-site, via satellite and over the Internet, as well as the transportation of auctioned automobiles and the financing services for the members of automobile auctions, among others. The Used Automobile Purchase and Sale segment is engaged in the purchase and sale of used automobiles and accident-damaged vehicles. The Others segment is engaged in the recycling of end-of-life vehicles and waste rubber, as well as the agency operations of export procedures for used automobiles. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries and two associated companies.

MEIDENSHA CORPORATION is primarily engaged in the development, production and sale of business systems. The Company operates in four segments. The Social System segment offers electric quality and energy-saving solutions, manufactures and sells electrical equipment, and provides treatment systems for water system. The Industrial System segment offers automobile testing and logistics systems, motors and inverters, and components products such as industrial computers and network systems for information industries. The Engineering segment provides energy-saving methods, remote management of equipment, maintenance services for semiconductor manufacturing devices, and the reproduction of used machines. The Real Estate segment leases real estate of ThinkPark Tower. In addition, the Company is also engaged in the provision of employees' welfare services and the manufacture and sale of chemical products. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 51 subsidiaries and four associated companies.

FUJI MACHINE MFG. CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of electronic part assembly machinery and machine tools. The Company operates in three business segments. The Electronic Part Assembly Machinery segment manufactures and sells automated placement equipment for electronic parts. The Machine Tool segment manufactures and sells specialty machinery and automated lathes. The Others segment is involved in the manufacture and sale of control devices, as well as the contract production of electronic circuit boards and the development of software. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had seven subsidiaries and one associated company.

BROTHER INDUSTRIES, LTD. is a Japan-based company engaged in the manufacture and sale of office equipment and supplies. The Company operates in six business segments. The Printing and Solutions segment manufactures and sells printers, multifunction devices, fax machines, electronic stationery and typewriters, among others. The Personal and Home segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of household sewing machines. The Machinery and Solution segment manufactures and sells industrial sewing machines, machine tools and other industrial equipment. The Network and Contents segment is involved in the manufacture, sale and service of commercial karaoke equipment, and the provision of contents delivery services. The Industrial component segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of speed reducer and gear. The Others segment is involved in the distribution of other products and the sale and leasing of real estate.

Yossix Co.,Ltd. is a Japan-based company engaged in food business, which includes direct management of pub chain and franchised store development. The Company operates pub chains under various brands, including Nipachi, Yataiya, Yataizushi, Sento, Koreya, Yakiniku Genki, providing Sushi, iron-plate cooking, chicken black charcoal and others. The Company operates its stores in Kanto, Chubu, Kansai and Kyushu areas.

MUSASHI SEIMITSU INDUSTRY CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of automobile motor parts, suspension parts and steering parts. The Company's Ball Joint business provides suspension arms assemblies, suspension ball joints and steering ball joints, among others. Its Camshaft business provides camshafts. Its Gear business provides planetary gear assemblies, bevel gears, helical gears, sprockets, gear shafts and con rods, among others. The Company has five regional segments, including Japan, North America, Europe, Asia and South America. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 18 subsidiaries.
