OKAYA&CO., LTD. mainly offers steel products. The Steel segment provides iron scraps, steel bars, steel piles, wide flange beams, steel plates, steel pipes and carbon steels for machinery structure. The Information and Electric segment provides rare earths, electronic parts, raw materials for aluminum, general-purpose electrical products, video equipment, semiconductors and electronic-related products, as well as develops and sells software. The Industrial Materials segment offers machine tools, industrial tools and robots, automobile parts, synthetic resin materials, resin molding products, environment and recycling treatment facilities, as well as semiconductors and electronics-related facilities and equipment. The Living Industry segment is involved in the manufacture and sale of piping, housing materials and housing equipment, the development of real estate, and warehouse businesses. As of February 28, 2014, the Company had 69 consolidated subsidiaries and 14 associated companies.

TAKAKITA CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacturing and sale of agricultural machinery, as well as the processing of bearings. The Company operates in two business segments. The Agriculture Machinery segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of agricultural machinery, such as machines for soil cultivation, forage harvesters and processing machines, feeding machines and snow removal machines. The Bearing segment is engaged in the customized processing of bearings.

CHITA KOGYO CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of spring products. The Company operates its businesses through two business divisions. The Spring Manufacturing division is primarily engaged in the manufacture and sale of lamina springs, wire springs, pipe molding products, cutting products and others for motorcycles, automobiles and industry machinery. The Others division is engaged in the supply of raw materials. In addition, the Company is engaged in the manufacture and sale of rubber products for industrial uses, as well as the purchase, processing and sale of buffered hardware. As of February 28, 2014, the Company had four consolidated subsidiaries and two associated companies.

MELCO HOLDINGS INC. is a Japan-based holding company mainly engaged in the development, manufacture and sale of digital consumer electronics and computer peripherals, as well as the provision of Internet-related services. Through its subsidiaries, the Company offers memory modules, universal serial bus (USB) flash memory products, storage products, network hard disks, wireless local area network (LAN) products, digital home products and supply accessories, among others. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had 18 subsidiaries. On February 3, 2014, the Company established a Tokyo-based wholly owned subsidiary engaged in the management of finance business. On June 30, 2014, the Company fully acquired BIOS Co.,Ltd.

FUJI HENSOKUKI CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of transmission and reduction gears. The Company operates in three business segments. The Reduction Gear-related segment manufactures and sells reduction gears, shutter switches and electric shutter hydraulic pressure release equipment. The Parking System-related segment is engaged in the design, construction, sale, maintenance and inspection of mechanical multi-level parking systems. The Interior and Exterior Products-related segment manufactures and sells movable partitions.

KOA CORPORATION is a company engaged in the manufacture of electronic components. It is principally involved in the manufacture and sale of electronic components such as circuit components including resistors, integrated circuits (ICs) and composite parts. The Company also offers products including surface mount device (SMD) resistors, leaded resistors, network resistors, negative temperature coefficient/positive temperature coefficient (NTC/PTC) thermistors, thermal sensors, inductors, fuses, varistors, low-temperature co-fired ceramic (LTCC) multilayer substrates and hybrid integrated circuits (ICs), among others. The Company operates throughout Japan, Asia, America and Europe. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 18 subsidiaries and one associated company.

Hitachi, Ltd. is engaged in providing solutions to customers in a range of sectors, including power/energy, industry/distribution/water, urban development, and finance/government and public/healthcare. The Company's segments include Information & Telecommunication Systems, Social Infrastructure & Industrial Systems, Electronic Systems & Equipment, Construction Machinery, High Functional Materials & Components, Automotive Systems, Smart Life & Ecofriendly Systems, Others (Logistics and Other services) and Financial Services. It provides solutions for corporate information technology (IT) strategies, IT platform solutions, and customized solutions and packaged software. It also offers products and services, such as industrial machinery and plants, elevators, escalators, and transmission and distribution systems. It supplies production and inspection equipment for the semiconductors and other electronic devices. It also offers optical disk drives and property management services.

TOYOTA BOSHOKU CORPORATION is a company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of automobile parts and textile products. The Company offers automobile interior components, such as seats, door trims, instrument panels, ceilings and illumination; filter/ power train equipment and parts, such as intake system parts, lubrication system parts and air conditioning system parts, among others; as well as fiber products and exterior products. On July 19, 2013, the Company acquired shares in TB Kawashima Co., Ltd. On October 25, 2013, it announced that it has acquired a China-based company as its subsidiary.

IMASEN ELECTRIC INDUSTRIAL CO., LTD. is a Japan-based manufacturer of automobile parts. The Company operates in five business segments. The Automobile Parts segment manufactures and sells automobile mechanical products, including seat adjusters and window regulators, as well as electric components, such as lamps, relays and horns. The Wire Harness segment manufactures and sells wire harnesses for aircraft and machine tool use. The Welfare Equipment segment manufactures and sells electric wheelchairs, prosthetic hands, prosthetic legs and other healthcare equipment. The Others segment is engaged in the provision of welfare services for employees. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 15 subsidiaries and one associated company.

MISAWA HOMES CO.,LTD. is a Japan-based housing construction company which has four business segments. The Group Business Planning and Management segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of prefabricated housing, planning and management for procurement and production of housing materials, design, construction planning and management of prefabricated housing. The Sale and Management segment is engaged in the provision of prefabricated housing materials, construction and sale of prefabricated housing, land sale, renovation and reconstruction works, rental management of apartments and condominiums, the operation of real estate information network, advertising agency business, and the operation of elderly welfare facilities. The Production and Logistics segment purchases and delivers construction materials. The Research, Development and Investigation segment is engaged in the housing-related research, development and investigation businesses.

Panasonic Industrial Devices SUNX Co., Ltd., formerly Panasonic Electric Works SUNX Co., Ltd., is a Japan-based company engaged in the development, design, manufacture and sale of sensing and control equipment, processing machinery, eco-friendly and custom goods. The Sensing and Control segment manufactures sensors for factory automation (FA) uses, programmable logic controllers and programmable indicators. The Processing Machinery segment is engaged in the provision of laser markers, image processors and ultraviolet cure devices, among others. The Eco and Custom Product segment is engaged in the manufacture of eco-related products, timers, counters and other custom products. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had four subsidiaries.

PACIFIC INDUSTRIAL CO., LTD. is a Japan-based manufacturer involved in three business segments. The Pressed and Resin Product segment manufactures and sells pressed and resin products for automobiles, as well as pressed molds and resin molds. The Valve Product segment manufactures and sells tire valves, valve core products, and various valves for air conditioning, tire-pressure monitoring systems (TPMSs), compressor-related products and electronic products. The Others segment is engaged in the operation of golf courses, the development, purchase and sale of software, the computer information processing and the non-life insurance agency businesses, among others. The Company offers its products in overseas markets in Taiwan, South Korea, the United States, Thailand and Mainland China. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 15 subsidiaries and one affiliated company.

JAPAN MATERIAL Co., Ltd. is primarily engaged in manufacturing specialty gas supply devices and providing piping work and related services. The Electronics segment is engaged in infrastructure field of specialty gases, ultrapure water, chemical liquid and others, which are essential for manufacturing process in plants of semiconductor, liquid crystal and secondary battery. It manufactures specialty gas supply devices, provides design and construction work of supply piping, and provides related services such as specialty gas sales management service, inspection, maintenance, operation and management, and other technical support service. The Graphics segment is engaged in sales of graphics boards for computers, and video related products, development of three-dimension software tools of CADCAM, contract development of three-dimensional data processing applications, and sales of CAD viewer software. On April 28, 2014, it established a Japan-based subsidiary.

Sumitomo Electric Industries, Ltd. is a Japan-based manufacturing company. It has five segments. The Automobile-related segment offers wire harnesses, rubber cushions, hoses for automobiles, automobile electrical parts and others. The Information Communications-related segment offers fiber-optic cables, electrical cables and equipment for communications use, optical communications-related parts and others. The Electronics-related segment offers electronic wires, compound semiconductors, flexible print circuit boards, fluorine resin products and others. The Environment Energy-related segment is engaged in the provision of conductive products, electric wire cables and equipment, coil wires and air springs, as well as the electrical construction works. The Industrial Material and Other segment offers steel wires for precision springs, steel rods, carbide tools and optical parts for lasers.

FUJI SEIKO LIMITED is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of carbide tools. The Company operates in four business segments. The Japan segment manufactures and sells carbide tools, including holders, tips, turning tools, cutters, drills, reamers and others, prototype parts for automotives, as well as metallic molds in Japan domestic market. The Asia segment mainly manufactures and sells carbide tools in Korea and China. The North and Central America segment mainly offers carbide tools in the United States. The Oceania segment sells carbide tools, manufactures and sells buffering, packaging and lagging materials, as well as air cell mats. The Others segment manufactures and sells carbide tools in Europe. As of February 28, 2014, the Company had 10 subsidiaries and two associated companies.

ATOM CORPORATION is principally engaged in the operation of restaurant chains. The Company operates in four business segments. The Restaurant segment operates restaurants which offer Sushi, grilled meat, steak, Japanese food, western food, pork cutlet, shabushabu (thin slices of beef parboiled in hot soup), ramen and others. The Izakaya segment operates Izakaya (Japanese-style bar) restaurants. The Entertainment segment is engaged in the operation of Karaoke (singing to taped accompaniment). The Others segment is engaged in the provision of operation guidance to franchised stores, and others.

Sintokogio, Ltd. is a manufacturing company engaged in six business segments. The Casting segment offers casting machines, vacuum-sealed processing equipment, molding sand processing equipment, automatic pouring equipment, casting shot blasting machines and related components. The Surface Treatment segment offers shot blasting machines, air blasting machines, shot peening machines, barrel grinders, precise brush polishing equipment, high precision microfabricated devices, polishing materials and others. The Environment segment offers dust collecting equipment, deodorization equipment, muffling devices and others. The Carrier segment offers lifting and lowering devices, gravity conveyors, transportation systems and others. The Special Equipment segment offers inspecting and measuring devices, servo-cylinders, liquid crystal display (LCD) panel manufacturing equipment and others. The Others segment is engaged in the design of machinery, and the information-related and welfare businesses.

NISSEI CORPORATION is a Japan-based manufacturer of reducers and gears. The Company operates its business through three segments. The Reducers segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of reducers. The Gears segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of gears, as well as the heat treatment and processing of gears. The Real Estate Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing of real estate properties. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had three subsidiaries.

AICHI CORPORATION is a Japan-based company, principally engaged in the sale of specially equipped vehicles, and the dealing of components. The Company provides digger derricks and aerial work platforms for the power supply, electrical and communication works, as well as aerial work platforms for construction and cargo handling. The Company also manufactures and distributes skid-steer loaders and parts, as well as repair services. The Company distributes its products in both domestic and overseas markets. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had four subsidiaries and one associated company.

NISSEI PLASTIC INDUSTRIAL CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company engaged in the manufacture and sale of injection molding machines, peripheral equipment, parts and dies. The Company's products include new type electric injection molding machines, plastic injection molding machines and molding systems, among others. Through its subsidiaries, the Company is also engaged in the non-life insurance agency business and factoring business. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 15 subsidiaries located in Japan, the United States, Singapore, Malaysia, Taiwan, Mexico, Hong Kong, Thailand and Mainland China.

SHIBUYA KOGYO CO., LTD. is primarily engaged in packing plant business. The Packaging Plant segment manufactures and sells washers, sterilization machines, filling machines, capping machines, labeling machines, cargo loading machines, conveyors, carton formers and sealing machines. The Mechatronics System segment provides laser application systems, such as laser processing machines and laser marking systems; semiconductor manufacturing systems, such as solder ball placement equipment; medical equipment, such as laser surgery equipment, cure equipment and dialysis systems. The Agricultural Equipment segment offers agricultural sorting and screening systems. The Others segment offers environmental equipment and systems, as well as the hot water jet washing machines.

Minebea Co., Ltd. is engaged in the manufacturing of miniature ball bearings, and also manufactures other highâˆ’precision parts. The Company's products include various input, conversion and control devices, such as switches, sensors and connectors. It operates through two segments: Machined Components Segment, and Electronic Devices and Components Segment. Its Machined Components Segment includes bearings, bearing-related products and machined components. Its Electronic Devices and Components Segment includes rotary components; electronic devices and components, and measuring components. The Company offers bearings, including miniature and small sized ball bearings; rod end and spherical bearings; roller bearings, which are related to aircraft flight control; roller bearings, which are related to aircraft engine; bushings; precision machined parts for aircraft, and medium-and large-sized ball bearings, which are used for aerospace; bearing-related products, and machined components.

AICHI ELECTRIC CO., LTD. is mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of electric power equipment and rotating machines. The Company operates in two business segments. The Electric Power Equipment segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of various transformers and switchboards, as well as the operation of power equipment works, and power generation, substation, transmission and communication-related works. The Rotating Machine segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of small motors, such as hermitic motors; shutter openers, actuators and printed circuit boards (PCBs). As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 12 subsidiaries and two associated companies.

DENSO Corporation is a supplier of automotive technology, systems and components for automakers. The Company's segments include Japan, North America, Europe, Asia and Others. It is organized into business groups, including Powertrain Control, which is engaged in the development and production of gasoline and diesel engine control systems; Thermal, which is engaged in the development and production of air-conditioning systems; Information and Safety Systems, which is engaged in the development and production of air-conditioning systems; Electronic, which is engaged in the development and production of semiconductor sensors and microelectronic devices; Small Motors, which is engaged in the development and production of windshield wiper systems; Industrial Systems, which is engaged in the development and production of bar code, and industrial robots, and Consumer Products, which is engaged is engaged in the development and production of carbon dioxide refrigerant heat-pump water heaters.

NIPPON STEEL & SUMITOMO METAL CORPORATION is a steel company. Its Steel Manufacturing segment engages in the manufacture and sale of steel bars, pipes and secondary steel products. Engineering segment engages in the construction of steel manufacturing plants, industrial machinery and furnaces, and environmental facilities. Chemical segment offers pitch coke, naphthalene, phthalic anhydride, carbon black and materials for liquid crystal displays (LCDs). New Material segment offers rolled metal foils and bonding wires for semiconductors. System Solution segment provides engineering consultation services on computer systems. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 337 subsidiaries and 109 associated companies.

MINO CERAMIC CO., LTD. is a Japan-based manufacturing company. The Company operates in five business segments. The Refractory segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of bricks, irregular refractory products and others, as well as the production of ceramic products. The Plant segment is engaged in the design and construction of manufacturing plants. The Construction and Paving Materials segment is engaged in the construction and sale of materials, as well as the manufacture and provision of paving materials and processed products. The Real Estate Leasing segment leases offices. The Others segment is engaged in the sale of outsourced goods. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries.

JTEKT Corporation is a Japan-based manufacture company. The Company operates in two business segments. The Machinery and Equipment segment manufactures and sells steering and driving system components, including electric power steering and hydraulic power steering systems, drive shafts and four-wheel drive (4WD) electronic control couplings, as well as bearings, including ball bearings, roller bearings, bearing units, among others. The Machine Tools segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of grinding machines, cutting machines, machining centers, controlling equipment and industrial heat-treating furnaces. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 143 subsidiaries and 21 associated companies.

Kobe Steel, Ltd. is a steel manufacturer. The Iron and Steel segment manufactures and sells steel bars, stainless-steel products and titanium products. The Welding segment offers welding materials, welding robots, and conducts welding-related consulting business. The Aluminum and Copper segment offers rolled aluminum products, rolled copper products, aluminum alloy products, magnesium alloy products and others. The Machinery segment manufactures and sells various energy, chemical and nuclear power-related equipment. The Engineering segment conducts engineering works and provides new transportation systems. The Kobelco Eco-Solutions provides water treatment plants, chemical and food-related equipment. The Kobelco Construction Machinery segment offers hydraulic and mini excavators. The Kobelco Crane segment provides crawler cranes and rough terrain cranes. The Others segment develops and leases real estate.

AISAN INDUSTRY CO., LTD. is principally engaged in the manufacture and sale of automotive parts. The Company operates in two business segments. The Automotive Parts segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of automotive parts, including fuel pump modules, throttle bodies, injectors and canisters, among others. The Non-automotive Parts segment is engaged in the automobile transportation business, the engineering and construction business, as well as the development and sale of computer systems and programs. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 25 subsidiaries and two associated companies.

CHUO MALLEABLE IRON CO., LTD. is a Japan-based manufacturer of metal made products. The Company operates in two business segments. The Malleable Casting segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of automobile parts and industrial machinery parts made from iron and aluminium. The Metallic Furniture segment is mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of office chairs. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had three consolidated subsidiaries and five associated companies.

Taihei Machinery Works, Limited is a Japan-based manufacturing company. The Company operates in three business segments. The Plywood Machinery segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of plywood machinery. The Woodworking Machinery segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of woodworking machinery. The Housing Materials segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of housing construction materials. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had one subsidiary.

NITTO KOGYO CORPORATION is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of switchboard-related products. The Company operates in three business segments. The Switchboard-related segment manufactures and sells switchboards, cabinets, breakers, switches and parts, among others. This segment is also involved in the design and drawing of switchboards/distribution switchboards and controlling boards, as well as the provision of manpower dispatch services. The Information- and communications-related Distribution segment purchases and sells information communication equipment. The Work and Service segment involves the construction of electrical equipment and network systems, and the provision of maintenance service. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 12 subsidiaries.

NAKANIPPON CASTING CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly involved in the casting business. The Company has two business segments. The Casting segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of automobile parts, hydraulic components, general engine parts, electrical components and pump components. The Others segment is engaged in the provision of maintenance services of heat exchangers, as well as the manufacture and sale of tools. The Company also engaged in solar power generation business.

Japan PC Service Co.,Ltd. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the provision of setting installation and troubleshooting of network-enabled devices, such as computers, tablet devices and digital consumer electronics. Its Smart Life Support segment has been divided into two divisions. The Field Support business is involved in the operation of directly operated stores and member stores, providing support services in major cities in Kanto, Kansai, Chubu and Kyushu. Its Membership Support Center business mainly involves in the provision of setting and failure correspondence services for network-enabled devices including computers in its call center by telephone or remote (remote control). This business is targeted at alliance companies that have entered into a contract with the Company.

DAIKOKU DENKI CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the development, manufacture and sale of computer systems targeting at pachinko (Japanese pinball) halls and components. The Company operates in two business segments. The Information Systems segment is involved in the development, manufacture and sale of computer systems, gift products and customer management systems, as well as information disclosure systems for pachinko halls. The Control Systems segment is engaged in development, manufacture and sale of display units and control units of pachinko game machines, the design, development, manufacture and sale of pachi-slot (Japanese slot) game machines, as well as the sale of game machine parts. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had two subsidiaries.

TOKAI RIKA CO., LTD. is mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of automobile parts. The Company provides automobile field products including switches, seatbelts, key locks, shift levers, automobile mirrors, steering wheels and decorations, as well as non-vehicle field products including entrance immobilizers, window lock monitoring systems and others.

FUJI ELECTRIC CO., LTD. is a manufacturer of industrial equipment. Power Generation and Social Infrastructure division provides thermal, geothermal and hydroelectric power generation equipment, energy management systems and nuclear-related equipment, among others. Industrial Infrastructure division offers industrial drive systems, measurement systems, industrial power systems and others. Power Electronics segment provides inverters, servo, motors and uninterruptible power supply (UPS), among others. Electronic Device segment offers power semiconductors, photoconductors and solar cells. Food Distribution segment offers food and beverage vending machines, distribution systems and currency-related equipment. Others segment engages in the real estate, insurance agency, travel businesses, as well as the provision of financial, printing and information and temporary staffing services. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 98 subsidiaries and 27 associated companies.

JX Holdings, Inc. is a holding company mainly engaged in petroleum business. The Energy segment is engaged in the processing, manufacture and sale of petroleum products and petrochemical products, the storage and transportation of crude and refined products, the investment in coal mining and sales companies, the sale of liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) products, power generation and power supply business and others. The Petroleum and Natural Gas Development segment is involved in the mining, development and production of petroleum and natural gas. The Metal segment offers nonferrous metal and electrical material processed products, nonferrous metal recycling services and industrial waste processing services and others. The Others segment involves in the civil engineering works, manufacture and sale of titanium and cables, and the sale, leasing and management of real estate, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 142 subsidiaries and 31 associated companies.

VLC HOLDINGS CO., LTD. is primarily engaged in providing consulting and solution service for security and building of systems and databases. The Consulting segment provides consulting service for information security such as personal information protection, and support service for establishing internal control. The Marketing Research segment provides marketing research utilizing Internet, consulting on business strategy, sales promotion and advertising agency services. The Information Digital Service segment provides support service for building of databases, and support service for libraries. The IT segment provides system proposal, development and operation support, and also provides value-added systems such as solutions utilizing original package software. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had four subsidiaries. On March 31, 2014, the Company transferred all shares in an 80.8%-owned subsidiary NDK Co., Ltd.

Alpen Co., Ltd. is a company principally engaged in the manufacture and sale of sports products. The Company operates in two business segments. The Retail segment is engaged in the sale of winter products, including ski equipment and snowboarding equipment; golf products, as well as general sports products, including training and fitness equipment, camping and tracking equipment, casual wear, marine goods, tennis and table tennis rackets, and items for baseball and soccer. The Others segment is involved in the provision of credit card services, and the operation of fitness clubs, ski and golf courses. As of June 30, 2012, the Company had six subsidiaries. On August 17, 2012, the Company established a Shanghai-based wholly owned subsidiary.

21LADY Co., Ltd. is a company mainly engaged in the operation of a chain of confectionary stores. The Company operates in three business segments. The HIROTA segment is mainly engaged in the operation of HIROTA, a chain of confectionary stores that mainly provides cream puffs and ice cream puffs, as well as the manufacture and sale of confectionary to supermarkets and convenience stores. The ILLUMS segment is engaged in the operation of stores and the sale of furniture, interior decorations and kitchenware. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had two subsidiaries.

Komehyo Co., Ltd. is a company mainly engaged in the brand fashion business. The Company has three business segments. The Brand Fashion segment is involved in the purchase and sale of used and new products, including jewelry, precious metal, watches, bags, clothing, cameras, musical instruments and other products. The Tire and Wheel segment is involved in the sale of tires, aluminum wheels and automotive parts, as well as the sale of reused products and outlet goods. The Others segment is engaged in the leasing of real estate properties. On May 9, 2013, the Company established an Aichi-based wholly owned subsidiary, which engaged in the planning and sale of automobile components and accessories. In July 2013, it established KOMEHYO HONG KONG LIMITED.

TOYODA GOSEI CO., LTD. is a company primarily engaged in the manufacture and sale of automobile parts and optoelectronic products. The Company operates in three business segments. The Automobile Parts segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of interior and exterior parts, such as instrument panels and console boxes; body sealing products; functionality parts, including functionality system components and fuel tank modules; safety system products, such as handles and air bag modules, as well as metal molds and machinery, among others. The Optoelectronic Product segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of high luminosity light-emitting diode lamp chip for liquid crystal backlights/ illumination light source. The Others segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of mobile phone chassis and air cleaners, among others.

CROSS PLUS INC. is engaged in the planning, production and sale of ladies' clothing. The Manufacturing and Sales group is engaged in wholesale business, which plans and sells clothing, furnishings, general merchandise and other clothing-related products. This group is also engaged in the original equipment manufacturing (OEM) supply business. The Specialty Store Retailer of Private Label Apparel (SPA) group is engaged in the planning, production and retail of clothing with various brand concepts. The Shibuya 109 Style SPA business plans, produces and sells clothing, furnishings and general merchandise targeted at young ladies. It has brands including LIZ LISA, TRALALA and LIZ LISA doll. The Career and Mrs business plans, produces and sells clothing, furnishings and general merchandise based on designer's brands and original brands concepts. On November 1, 2012, it took over all businesses from its wholly owned subsidiary, engaged in the planning, manufacturing and sale of lady clothes.

IHI Corporation manufactures an enormous range of products. The Resources, Energy and Environment division provides boilers, storage facilities, nuclear power equipments. The Social Infrastructure and Marine division provides bridges, floodgates, shield machines and marine structures, as well as operates real estate business. The Industrial System and General Machinery division provides marine machinery, logistics systems, transportation machinery, parking, steel machinery, industrial machinery, among others. The Aerospace and Defense division provides aviation engine, rocket systems and space utilization, defense equipment systems and others. The Others division provides communication, electronic, electrical measurement, information processing equipments and devices, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 148 subsidiaries and 35 associated companies.

Janis Ltd. is a Japan-based company engaged in the manufacture and sale of sanitary equipment. The Company is engaged in the manufacture and sale of sanitary ware, including closet bowls, urine basins, wash-basins and water basins; toilet seats, including toilet seats with warm water washers, toilet seats with heaters and general toilet seats; counters, including water basins with counter and water basins with cabinets; accessories, including paper holders, towel rings, storage rack, and others. The Company also offers bathroom vanities and dressing tables, among others.

Chubu Steel Plate Co.,Ltd. is a Japan-based iron and steel manufacturer. The Company operates in four business segments. The Steel-related segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of thick plate steel products, using purchased iron scrap. The Rental segment is engaged in the rental of grease filters for commercial kitchens, and the operation of advertising billboard business. The Logistics segment is engaged in the provision of transportation and cargo handling services, as well as the warehousing of dangerous goods. The Engineering segment is engaged in the design and construction of plants, as well as the provision of engineering services, such as equipment maintenance. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had four subsidiaries.

TOYO ELECTRIC CORPORATION is principally engaged in the manufacture and sale of industrial electronic control systems. The Company operates in three business segments. The Domestic Control Device-related segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of monitoring control systems, switchboards, transformers, sensors and indicators. The Overseas Control Device-related segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of switchboards and elevator sensors. The Resin-related segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of road traffic safety materials, including guard fences, and guard pipes and resin pallets. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had five subsidiaries.

KANESO Co., LTD. is primarily engaged in manufacturing and selling metal products for use in construction. The Company manufactures and sells castings, steel parts, fabricated hardware and others, such as expansion joints, drains and manholes, for use in construction such as buildings, welfare facilities, greening and city landscaping. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had one subsidiary.

OWARI PRECISE PRODUCTS CO., LTD. is primarily engaged in manufacturing precision forgings, screws (primarily for automobiles) and aircraft parts. The Japan segment is engaged in manufacturing nuts for welding, self-locking nuts, screw products, metal fittings and nuts for construction, and others. The America segment is engaged in manufacturing and supplying small screws for automobile manufacturers in the North America. The India segment is engaged in manufacturing and supplying synchronizer rings and shafts for automobile manufacturers in Asia. The Thailand segment is engaged in manufacturing and supplying shift forks and synchronizer rings for automobile manufacturers in Asia. As of March 31, 2015, the Company had six subsidiaries.

Kajima Corporation is engaged in the construction (civil engineering and building construction), real estate development, architectural design, civil engineering design, engineering, and other. The Company's segments include Civil Engineering, Building Construction, Real Estate Development, and Overseas Construction and Development. The Company serves as both project developer and contractor. The Company has a network of overseas subsidiaries and affiliates in North America, Asia and Europe providing building construction and/or real estate development business. The Company offers various technology and services, such as The Kajima Cut and Take Down Method; KAJIMA DESIGN; Kajima Technical Research Institute; Great Hanshin Earthquake Review; Kajima's Advanced Structural Control and Base Isolation Technologies; Himeji Castle Main Keep, and Engineering Services.

TEAR Corporation is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the funeral business. The Company operates in two business segments. The Funeral segment is engaged in the implementation of funeral ceremonies at 33 directly-managed funeral halls, individual homes, temples and community centers for individual customers and others mainly in Nagoya city and nearby areas of Aichi Prefecture. This segment is also engaged in the provision of Buddhist memorial services for end of mourning and anniversary of death after the funeral ceremonies. The Franchise segment is engaged in the franchise business, such as the support of market research, funeral home planning, employee training and operational guidance for the funeral home operations.

KeePer Technical Laboratory Co., Ltd is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the car washing business. The Company operates its business in two segments. Its KeePer Products-related segment manufactures chemical products for car coating uses and tools for professional use, sells its products to car washing stores. Its KeePer Operation segment involves in the operation of KeePer LABO stores, providing car coating services.

NIPPON SHARYO, LTD. has four business segments. The Railway Cars segment manufactures and sells trains, diesel railcars, passenger cars, linear motor cars. The Transportation Equipment and Steel Structure segment manufactures and sells freight cars, locomotives, tanker lorries, tank trailers, containers and automated guide-way transit systems, as well as manufactures, constructs and sells highway bridges, railway bridges and sluices. The Construction Equipment segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of piling machines, crawler cranes and diesel generator sets and others, as well as the sale and repair of construction machinery. The Others segment manufactures and sells vehicle inspection and repair facilities, linear-related facilities, agricultural plants and paper making-related equipment. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had eight subsidiaries and five associated companies.

TAIYO KAGAKU CO., LTD. is a food manufacturer. The Nutrition division offers green tea-related products such as catechin and functional food materials, as well as vitamins, minerals and polyunsaturated fatty acid (PUFA). The Interface Solution division offers emulsifiers, emulsion stabilizers, emulsifier preparations, emulsified food, stabilizers and chemical products. The Agri-food division offers processed egg products, protein ingredients, modifiers for processed food, materials for instant food, dried food, processed fruit products and processed agricultural products. The Others division is engaged in the cooking and beverage related business. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 11 subsidiaries and three associated companies.

Chuo Seisakusho, Ltd. is a company mainly engaged in the manufacture of power-supply equipment. The Power-Supply Equipment segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of power-supply equipment with a focus on direct-current (DC) power supply devices for industrial and academic use. The Surface Processing Device segment offers surface processing devices for coating, alumite treatment, chemical conversion treatment and electrophoretic coating, among others. The Electrical Welder segment provides electrical welding devices with a focus on spot welders. The Environmental Equipment segment offers effluent treatment machines and ion-exchange equipment. The Others segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of electrolytic machines, the development of electrolytic processing technology, and others.

Hino Motors, Ltd. is a manufacturer of trucks and buses in Japan. The Company manufactures heavy- and medium-duty trucks, as well as light-duty trucks. The Company's segments include Japan and Asia. The Company is also engaged in production on commission for Toyota Motor Corporation and other services, such as development and planning of related products. The Company has market share in Southeast Asia and in Australia. Its global operations also serve a range of customers in Latin America and in other regions. The Company offers HINO300 Series, HINO500 Series and HINO700 Series trucks. Its trucks include HINO700 Series, HINO500 Series, HINO300 Series, HINO600 Series, HINO500 Series, Hybrid HINO300 Series Hybrid, Hybrid touring coach, Hybrid low-floor bus, Touring coach, Low-floor bus, Industrial engine E13C-TI and Industrial engine J08C-T. The Company also offers bus chassis, and develops and produces diesel engines for industrial applications

KIKUKAWA ENTERPRISE, INC. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the manufacture and sale of woodworking machineries and machine tools. The woodworking machineries include machines which can process logs into square timbers, plates and small split materials, and machines which can secondary process timbers, plates, small split materials, plywood and fiberboards into products. The machine tools refer to machines processing irons, non-ferrous metals and other new materials.

CK SAN-ETSU CO., Ltd. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of brass rods and wires, as well as precision parts made from brass rods and wires. The Company operates in three business segments. The Copper and Brass segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of brass rods, brass wires and brass tubes. The Precision Parts segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of camera mounts, flare nuts and sockets. The Piping and Gilt segment manufactures piping equipment and molten zinc plating. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had seven subsidiaries and one associated company.

JFE Holdings, Inc. is a holding company. The Steel segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of steel products, processed steel products and raw materials, as well as the delivery, facility maintenance and construction businesses. The Engineering segment is engaged in the engineering construction business related to energy, urban environment, recycling, steel structure and industrial machinery. The Trading segment provides steel products, welding materials, iron powder, steel processing products, steel raw materials and equipment, non-ferrous metal products, chemical products, petroleum products, paper products, marine, civil engineering and construction works, canned products, agricultural and livestock products, marine products, semiconductor products, as well as real estate, among others.

TSURUYA CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture of tiles products. The Company is engaged in the manufacture and sale of ceramics tiles; the contracted construction of roofing works; the sale of roofing materials, as well as other related businesses. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had one associated company.

ASAHI-SEIKI MANUFACTURING CO.,LTD. is a Japan-based manufacturing company. The Company is engaged in the operation of Precision Machining Division and Machinery Division, which manufacture and sell various precision metal processing products and machineries, including small-caliber bullets, precision metal processed goods, press equipment, aircraft parts, spring machinery, automated machinery and specialized machinery. It is also involved in the manufacture of molds. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had one unconsolidated subsidiary and one affiliated company.

NIKKO COMPANY is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of housing and environmental equipment, ceramics and functional ceramic products. The Company has four business segments. The Housing and Environmental Equipment segment is engaged in the maintenance of septic tanks. The Ceramics segment offers ceramics. The Functional Ceramic Products segment offers functional ceramic products. The Others segment offers resin forms and others.

Comany Inc. is a Japan-base company principally engaged in the manufacture and sale of various types of partition products. It operates in two business segments: Japan segment and China segment. Japan segment and China segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of wood products and components, as well as the provision of engineering services. The Company provides high partition products, low partition products, movable partitions, bathroom partitions, clean room partitions and door products, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had seven subsidiaries and one associated company.

MG HOME CO., LTD. is a Japan-based real estate company. The Company has two business segments. The Condominium segment is engaged in the planning, development and sale of condominiums. The Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing of 17 condominiums owned by the Company. The Company is based in Nagoya. On August 1, 2014, VT HOLDINGS CO LTD became its parent company.

KIMURA UNITY CO., LTD. is primarily engaged in logistics business. The Company operates in four business segments. The Logistics Service segment is engaged in packaging and packing, loading and unloading operations, and the manufacture of storage fixtures. The Automotive Services segment is engaged in the leasing and maintenance of automobiles, and the provision of insurance brokerage services. The Information Service segment is engaged in system development operations, comprehensive maintenance and network related services, among others. The Human Resource Service segment is engaged in the provision of temporary staffing services, outsourcing services and others. The Other segment is engaged in the solar power generation business. As of M arch 31, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries and five associated companies.

ICHIBANYA CO., LTD. is a company mainly engaged in the operation of curry specialty restaurants under the name Curry House CoCo Ichibanya. The Company is involved in the provision of curry dishes through directly-managed stores and franchise chain (FC) stores, as well as the sale of foodstuff, consumable supplies and equipment to FCs. In addition, the Company also involves in the franchise business, trade and consulting services through its subsidiaries. As of May 31, 2013, the Company had two consolidated subsidiaries and three associated companies.

MIRAI INDUSTRY CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in electric and pipe materials business. The Company operates in three business segments. The Electric and Pipe Materials segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of electric wires, tubes and accessories, wiring boxes, resin tubes for water and hot water supply, and accessories, as well as the provision of flooring work. The Wiring Accessories segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of switches, sockets and others. The Others segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of work saving equipment, molding dies and resin raw materials, the transportation business, the construction business, the telecommunication business, as well as the cable television (TV) business, among others. As of March 20, 2014, the Company had seven subsidiaries.

Dainihon Wood-Preserving Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in timber business. The Timbers segment is involved in the manufacture and sale of corrosion-proof bases used for wooden houses, and railroad ties; the sale of construction materials, such as pillars and beams; the sale of lumbers and plywood, and the processing and sale of wooden framing precut materials and panels. The Logistics segment is involved in the transportation and cargo handling activities. The Real Estate segment is involved in the rental of warehouses, condominium buildings and others. The Wood Insect Pest Control segment manufactures and sells agent for insect pest control and is engaged in the pest control work. The Company also involves in solar power generation business.

HOSHIZAKI CORPORATION, formerly HOSHIZAKI ELECTRIC CO., LTD., mainly provides kitchen instruments and related maintenance service. It is engaged in the research, development, manufacture and sale of ice makers, including fully-automatic and large-scale ice makers; freezing and refrigeration equipment, including fridge-freezers for business use and frozen refrigerator showcases; cleaning machines, including dish washers; hygiene management equipment, including electrolysis water generating devices and sterilizing cabinets; cooking appliances, including electromagnetic cookers, electronic frying equipment and microwaves; drinking service equipment, including dispensers, as well as food service equipment and freshness management equipment, among others.

The Takigami Steel Construction Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company engaged in the design, manufacture and sale of steel structure products. The Company operates in three business segments. The Steel Structure Products Manufacturing segment is engaged in the design, manufacture, processing and construction of steel bridges, iron frames and other steel structure products. The Real Estate Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing and management of real estate properties. The Others segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of bolts and nuts; the cutting, processing and sale of steel plates; the sale of shaped steel and other materials, as well as the transportation of steel bridges, iron frames and other steel structure products. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had one subsidiary, 10 associated companies and one affiliated company.

HIMARAYA Co., Ltd. is primarily involved in the sale of sports goods. The Company sells products in the fields of sportswear, running, walking, wellness, accessory, tennis, baseball, soccer, basketball, volleyball, golf, outdoor, active, ski, snow board and winter wear. As of August 31, 2014, the Company had one subsidiary and one affiliated company.

OKUMA Corporation is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of numeric control (NC) machine tools, machinery centers, multitasking machines and NC grinders. Through its subsidiaries and associated companies, the Company is engaged in the design, manufacture, sale and assembling of machine tools, as well as the provision of after services. It is also engaged in the manufacture and sale of precisive metal processed products, the manufacture of sheet-metal parts for machine tools and the management of plant buildings, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 23 subsidiaries and one associated company.

TOKAN CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the wholesale of food products. The Company is involved in the wholesale, manufacture and processing of food products, as well as the sale of daily necessities. Through its subsidiaries and associated companies, the Company is also engaged in the automobile transportation business and the warehouse business, the processing and sale of seaweed and shiitake mushrooms, the operation of foods wholesale business in China, the wholesale of food products and other various goods mainly in Aichi Prefecture, as well as the wholesale of alcohol products. As of September 30, 2014, the Company had four subsidiaries and two associated companies.

DOWA HOLDINGS CO., LTD. is a Japan-based holding company. The Company has six business divisions. The Environment and Recycling division is engaged in the operation of waste management, recycling, soil remediation and logistics businesses. The Smelting division manufactures and sells copper, zinc, gold, silver and other metals. The Electronic Materials division manufactures and sells electrical conducting material for electronic component, among others. The Metal Processing division manufactures and sells processed metal products, circuit boards. The Thermal Treatment division is engaged in the thermal treatment and surface treatment processing of metal materials, as well as the manufacture, sale and maintenance of thermal processing facilities and auxiliary facilities. The Others division is engaged in the real estate leasing business, plant construction works business and others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 89 subsidiaries and 19 associated companies.

The Aichi Bank, Ltd. is a Japan-based regional bank that is involved in the banking, securities, trust contract and leasing services. The Bank operates in three business segments. The Banking segment offers banking services, including deposit, loan, domestic and foreign exchange, trust investment and offering of life insurance services. This segment is also engaged in the provision of securities services, including securities trading, securities investment and intermediation, underwriting and registration of bonds, as well as specified donation, land, real estate property and equipment and pension trust services. The Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing business. The Others segment is engaged in the provision of computer-related processing and credit card services.

Shinwa Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based industrial machinery manufacturer. The Company is engaged in the sale of welding equipment, industrial machinery and factory automation (FA) systems, the weld cladding, thermal spraying and soldering activities, the manufacture and sale of FA systems, as well as the maintenance works. Through its subsidiaries, the Company is also involved in the real estate management and nonlife insurance agency businesses. The Company's main products include resistance welding equipment, laser welding equipment, electron beam welding equipment, control boards and operation panels, communication terminal modules, cable connectors, message display systems, industrial robots, dispensing detecting systems, cold forging machines and steel plate washing machines. As of August 31, 2012, the Company had 12 subsidiaries.

RINNAI CORPORATION is a Japan-based company engaged in the manufacture and sale of heating appliances and components. The Company provides kitchen appliances such as gas stoves, dish washers, gas hot water heaters, rice cookers and ovens; bath appliances, such as bathroom televisions (TVs), heaters and dryers and remote controls; living appliances, such as gas fan heaters, gas infrared heaters and floor heating systems; professional products such as gas grillers, gas fryers and gas ranges, as well as other products. The Company sells its products directly to utility gas companies, propane fuel distributors, housing equipment manufacturers, house makers, pipe and construction material distributors and general merchandising stores, as well as to overseas markets through its overseas subsidiaries.

FUTABA INDUSTRIAL CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company, primarily engaged in the manufacture and sale of automobile assembly parts, information environment equipment parts, as well as jigs and welding machines. The Company distributes its products in the domestic market and to the overseas markets including the North America, Europe and Asia. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 23 subsidiaries and five associated companies.

HAGIWARA ELECTRIC CO., LTD is mainly engaged in the sale of electronic components. The Company operates in two business segments. The Device Business Unit segment sells microprocessors, system large scale integration (LSI), analogs and power semiconductors, capacitors, relays, connectors and switches, designs system LSI, as well as conducts technology support business such as software development. The Solution Business Unit segment is involved in the problem-solving solution provision business include the information technology(IT) machinery provision and the application development, the solution provision business in measurement and IT platform and infrastructure construction fields, as well as the development and manufacture of electronic information products. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries.

SOTOH CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the dyeing, processing, manufacture and sale of textile products, as well as the leasing of real estate. The Company operates in three business segments. The Dyeing and Processing segment is engaged in the dyeing and processing of textile products. The Textile segment is involved in the manufacture and sale of textile products. The Real Estate Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing of shops for mass retailers. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries.

Makita Corporation is engaged in the business of production and sale of electric power tools, woodworking machines, pneumatic tools, gardening equipment and household equipment. The Company manufactures and sells portable electric planers. The Company's segments are Japan, Europe, North America, Asia and Other area. Its other areas include Central and South America, The Middle East and Africa, and Oceania. The Company's product categories include cordless, drilling/fastening, impact drilling/demolition, cutting (new material/masonry), cutting (metal), grinding/sanding, sawing, planing/routering, pneumatic tools, outdoor power equipment, dust extraction and others. Its subsidiaries include Makita U.S.A. Inc., Makita (U.K.) Ltd., Makita Werkzeug GmbH, Makita Oy, Makita (China) Co., Ltd. and Makita (Kunshan) Co., Ltd., among others.

KISOJI CO.,LTD. is mainly engaged in the restaurant business. The Company operates in six business divisions. The Kisoji division operates restaurants, which offer shabushabu (sliced beef boiled with vegetables) and Japanese foods. The Sozaiya division operates Izakaya (Japanese-style bars). The Suzu Noren division operates Japanese restaurants. The Torikaku division operates restaurants serving chicken dishes. The Janjantei division operates barbecue restaurants. The Others segment is involved in the operation of wine canteen under the name Uno, the sale of Shigure clam, as well as the leasing of real estate. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had over165 stores.

NAGOYA ELECTRIC WORKS CO., LTD. is a company engaged in the manufacture and sale of information devices and testing instruments. The Company operates in two business segments. The Information Device segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of light-emitting diode (LED) information systems for roads and rivers, disaster prevention systems for tunnels, mobile information vehicles, vehicle-mounted indicators, systems for parking lot information, information providing system under the name Michi no Eki, weather and disaster monitoring systems and variable regulatory sign systems and other systems, as well as the provision of maintenance and management services. The Testing Device segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of appearance testers for printed circuit boards (PCBs) and hardware testing devices. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had one consolidated subsidiary.

Aichi Tokei Denki Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of measuring equipment and other special equipment. The Measuring Instrument segment carries four types of products: gas-related equipment, which include utility gas meters, liquefied petroleum (LP) gas meters, industrial meters, pressure equipment, gas meter systems and others; water work-related equipment, including various water supply meters, industrial water meters and sewage meters, bill management systems, emergency report systems and others; civil sensors and systems, including flow instrument and flow sensors, as well as instrumentation which include measuring, monitoring and control systems. The Others segment manufactures and sells gears, components and precision dies for industrial machineries. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had 10 subsidiaries and four associated companies.

YAGAMI INC. is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the equipment manufacturing business. The Company has three business segments. The Scientific Equipment segment manufactures and sells wooden products such as laboratory benches, worktops, sterilizers and others. It is also engaged in the leasing of real estates. The Healthcare and Medical Equipment segment sells human body models for resuscitation training and visual acuity testing equipment and and others. The Industrial Equipment segment is engaged in the sale of electrical heaters for heat-retention and calefaction use, as well as the manufacture and sale of environmental testing equipment. As of April 20, 2014, the Company had two subsidiaries.

GIGA PRIZE CO., LTD. is primarily engaged in Internet-related services. HomeIT segment provides Internet service provider (ISP) and life support application service provider (ASP) service for condominium residents, and network services such as managed service provider (MSP) service and hosting service for corporations. The System Development segment is engaged in sale and contract development of application software for a range of business operators. In addition, the Company provides staffing service in management sector. As of March 31, 2013, the Company had two subsidiaries. On August 14, 2013, the Company sold a Tokyo-based subsidiary.

Kawasaki Heavy Industries, Ltd. provides environmental and recycling plants, industrial plants, precision machinery, industrial robots and infrastructure equipment. The Company's leisure and power products business includes motorcycles under the Kawasaki brand. It operates through eight segments: Ship & Offshore Structure, which is engaged in the construction and sale of ships and other vessels; Rolling Stock, which produces and sells rolling stock and snow plows; Aerospace, which produces and sells aircraft; Gas Turbines & Machinery, which produces and sells jet engines and prime movers, among others; Plant & Infrastructure, which produces and sells industrial equipment and environmental equipment, among others; Motorcycle & Engine, which produces and sells motorcycles and all-terrain vehicles, among others; Precision Machinery, which is engaged in the production and sale of industrial hydraulic products and industrial robots, and Other, which includes commercial activities.

Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group, Inc. (MUFJ) is a bank holding company. The Company's segments include Integrated Retail Banking Business Group, Integrated Corporate Banking Business Group, Integrated Trust Assets Business Group, Integrated Global Business Group and Krungsri. The Company's services include commercial banking, trust banking, securities, credit cards, consumer finance, asset management, leasing and various fields of financial services. The Company's subsidiaries include The Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ, Ltd. (BTMU), Mitsubishi UFJ Trust and Banking Corporation (MUTB), Mitsubishi UFJ Securities Holdings Co., Ltd. (MUSHD), Mitsubishi UFJ Morgan Stanley Securities Co., Ltd. (MUMSS) and Mitsubishi UFJ NICOS Co., Ltd. Its Retail Banking Business Group covers retail businesses, including commercial banking, trust banking and securities businesses, and offers a range of banking products and services, including financial consulting services, to retail customers in Japan.

Go Iron Works Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based company primarily engaged in the manufacture and sale of construction machinery and general industrial machinery. The Company is engaged in the purchase of lining-related materials, the manufacture of lining products, the sale and construction work of lining plumbing products, as well as the sale of sheet lining container products. The Company is also engaged in the purchase and sale of construction machinery and construction-related materials. Its products include hammer crushers, impact crushers, single toggle crushers, water treatment equipment, belt conveyors, cranes and various tools.

TOPY INDUSTRIES, LIMITED is an automobile and industrial machinery parts manufacturing company. Steel segment is engaged in the manufacture of steel products by using electrical furnace, and the production and sale of rolled steel products including wide flange beams, standard shaped steel and deformed bars. Automobile and Industrial Machinery Parts segment is engaged in the provision of automotive steel wheels, aluminum wheels, steel wheels for construction machinery, stamping products for automotive, industrial fasteners and industrial machine parts including undercarriage components of power shovels and bulldozers, and cutting edge of motor graders. Others segment is engaged in the wholesale of power supply, the provision of sign systems, synthetic mica and crawler robots, civil engineer and construction business, the leasing of real estates, the operation of sports facilities, and the provision of financial service.

TAIHO KOGYO CO., LTD. is a Japan-based manufacturer of automobile parts. The Company operates in three business segments. The Automobile Part-related segment manufactures and sells bearings, such as metal bushings, as well as other automobile components, including die cast, gaskets and solder products. This segment also distributes its products in the United States, Indonesia, Hungary, Korea, China, and Thailand. The Automobile Manufacturing Equipment-related segment is involved in the manufacture and sale of precision molds. Through its subsidiaries, this segment also supplies automobile manufacturing equipment, including carrier devices and welding machines, as well as molds and equipment components, among others. The Others segment is engaged in the building and repair work, the welfare business, as well as the packing and dispatch of automobile parts. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 16 subsidiaries, two associated companies and two non-consolidated subsidiaries.

Taiho Transportation Co., Ltd. operates in three business segments. The Cargo Transportation segment is engaged in the automobile transportation for food products, daily miscellaneous goods and consumption products in the areas of Aichi, Gifu, Mie and Shizuoka Prefectures. The Warehousing segment is engaged in the provision of general logistics services, such as the collection, storage, distribution processing, delivery and recovery of cargos. The Others segment is engaged in the inspection, regular overhaul and general repair for automobiles, the solar power generation business, the non-life insurance agency business and the leasing of building.

ASAHI INTECC CO., LTD. is a Japan-based company principally engaged in the development, manufacture and sale of medical and industrial equipment. The Company operates in two business segments. The Medical segment is involved in the development, manufacture and sale of minimally invasive treatment products (catheter related products) used in endovascular treatment. The Device segment develops, manufactures and sells supplies for medical and industrial equipment. As of June 30, 2014, the Company had eight consolidated subsidiaries. The Company is also engaged in the design, production and sale of finest wire manufacturing machine.

SUGI HOLDINGS CO., LTD. is a Japan-based holding company. The Company operates in two business segments. The Pharmacy segment is engaged in the sale of pharmaceuticals, health foods, cosmetics, daily necessaries and others, as well as the operation of regional medical handling drag stores which focus on home medical care. The Drug segment is engaged in the operation of drug stores which focus on the sale of daily necessaries and food, pharmaceuticals, health foods and cosmetics, among others. As of February 28, 2013, the Company had six subsidiaries.

Japan Best Rescue System Co., Ltd. is engaged in the provision of daily life rescue services. The Call Center segment offers key replacement services, automobile-related services and other life-related emergency services. The Membership segment offers motorcycle stolen compensation services and other daily problem solving services. The Corporation Collaboration segment offers representative call center and customer support services. The Member Store segment develops and manages stores and cooperation stores. The Small-amount and Short-term Insurance segment offers underwriting services for small-amount and short-term insurances. The Automobile Leasing segment leases automobiles. The Others segment offers support services for self-developed home security products. On February 27, 2013, it acquired a 46.2% stake of a Japan-based company. As a result, it hold a 58.6% stake in the Japan-based company up from 12.4% stake.

Kojima Iron Works Co., Ltd. is primarily engaged in build-to-order manufacturing of large presses. The Press segment provides hydraulic presses for sheet metal forming, slate forming, packing, hot forming and plastics forming, cantilever hydraulic presses, horizontal hydraulic benders, hydraulic riveters, hydraulic forging presses, hydraulic extrusion presses, hydraulic press brakes, and press-related products, among others. The Machinery Work segment provides equipment work of power generation, air conditioning, plumbing, hygiene, various conveyors, and others. The Real Estate Rental segment is engaged in rental of health facilities.

ISEWAN TERMINAL SERVICE CO., LTD. mainly operates harbor transportation business. Harbor Transportation segment offers harbor transportation services and cargo-handling services at ports, barge transportation services, shed storage services, as well as container terminal management services, among others. Warehousing segment offers warehouse storage and cargo handling services. Cargo Transportation segment offers cargo transportation services. Custom Clearance segment offers customs clearing services. Air Transportation Agency segment offers air transportation agency services. Packaging segment offers packaging services for export cargos. General and Industrial Waste Transportation and Recycle segment is engaged in the transportation and regeneration treatment of general and industrial wastes. General Trucking segment offers general trucking services. Others segment is engaged in the other transportation-related businesses.

TOKYO GAS CO., LTD. is a Japan-based gas company. It has five business segments. The City Gas segment is engaged in the production, supply and sale of gas. This segment is also engaged in the provision of gas to city gas providers, as well as the supply and sale of gas in Malaysia. The Instrument and Gas Fitting segment is engaged in the sale of gas appliances, and the gas fitting business, such as gas piping works. The Other Energy segment is engaged in the sale of liquefied petroleum gas (LPG), the wholesale of electricity, the provision of energy services, as well as the sale of industrial gas. The Real Estate segment specializes in the leasing of real estate. The Others segment is involved in the investment to overseas gas field development, the transportation of liquid natural gas(LNG) and LPG, the provision of information processing services, the construction of gas-related equipment, among others. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 69 subsidiaries and 67 associated companies.

TOKURA CORPORATION is a Japan-based construction company. The Company operates in five business segments. The Construction segment is engaged in the design, construction, maintenance and repair of build works of buildings, houses, factories, medical and welfare facilities, and commercial facilities, as well as the construction of schools and public facilities. The Civil Engineering segment is involved in various general civil engineering works and corporate land development. The Overseas segment provides overseas construction services. The Real Estate segment is involved in the trading and leasing of real estate, as well as construction business related service, such as building management and security service. The Others segment is involved in the sale and leasing of materials and equipment for construction activities, as well as the provision of food service for funeral halls and schools.

TOHO GAS CO., LTD. is a company primarily engaged in the gas business. The Company operates in four business segments. The Gas segment is engaged in the manufacture, supply and sale of gas in Aichi, Mie, Gifu and Okayama Prefectures. The Construction and Equipment segment is engaged in the provision of piping works for gas supply and the sale of gas equipment. The Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG) and Other Energy segment is engaged in the sale of liquefied natural gas (LNG), the supply of heat, the sale of LPG and LPG equipment, the provision of LPG piping works, as well as the sale of coke and petroleum products. The Others segment is involved in the leasing and operation of real estate, the design and construction and the provision of utility service for plants and facilities, the sale of household equipment, the provision of information processing services, the leasing of automobiles and equipment, and the sale of hot and cold LNG and liquefied nitrogen.

MARUEI DEPARTMENT STORE COMPANY, LIMITED is a Japan-based company mainly engaged in the operation of department stores. The Company operates in three business segments. The Department Stores segment offers clothing, food products, accessories, household goods and other products through its department stores. The Real Estate Leasing segment is engaged in the leasing of real estate properties such as offices and stores. The Others segment is engaged in the provision of transportation services, pre-paid voucher services and janitorial services through its subsidiaries. As of February 28, 2014, the Company had six subsidiaries and one associated company.

NICHIHA CORPORATION is a company mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of armoring materials. The Company operates in five business segments. The Armoring Material segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of armoring materials and external wall materials for ceramic industry, as well as metal armoring materials and templates. The FP segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of urethane insulation panels. The Fiber Board segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of fiber boards. The Construction segment is engaged in the operation of exterior finish works using the Company's products. The Others segment is engaged in the operation of maintenance business, cleaning business and industrial waste business related to the product manufacturing, as well as the provision of insurance agency service and temporary staffing service. As of March 31, 2014, the Company had 17 subsidiaries.

LIXIL Group Corp engages in building materials and equipment business, distribution and retail business, and housing services business. Its domestic business includes metal building materials business, plumbing equipment business, other building materials and equipment business, distribution and retail business, housing and real estate other business. Overseas business includes Asia business, curtain wall business, ASB and other businesses. The Metal Building Material segment provides sashes, shutters, curtain walls and doors. The Plumbing Fixture segment provides sanitary equipments, bathtubs, prefabricated baths, built-in kitchens and washing basins. The Other Building Material and Equipment segment provides woody interior materials including window cases; construction materials. The Distribution and Retail segment operates home centers and building material centers. The Housing, Real Estate and Others segment provides housing solutions.

VT HOLDINGS CO., LTD. is a Japan-based holding company. Along with its subsidiaries and associated companies, the Company operates in two business segments. The Automotive Sale-related segment is engaged in the sale and repair of new and used cars through Honda dealers, Nissan dealers, imported car dealers and car importers.
